(6224, 'Club 8', 'http://www.indievox.com/club8', 'http://cdn-data.indievox.com/indievox_user/30000/6224/pix/6224180X180.jpg?1427770883', 30, 'Club 8 八號會所，發跡自西班牙清新廠牌Siesta的動人音樂會所。\r\n「要是你喜歡Sarah Records，喜歡簡單而清新的吉他音樂，或是陽光充沛的早上，甚至是繁星滿天的晚上。我想，你也會喜歡Club 8。」-----香港MCB音樂雜誌。\r\n除了展現感傷之外對於美好流行旋律的熱愛，更在幾首流露Synth-Pop風華的作品中交織出Saint Etienne和Pet Shop Boys的流暢。\r\nAll-Music Guide音樂網站四顆星高評價肯定。\r\n\r\nclub 8 was formed in 1995 by Karolina Komstedt (from the band Poprace) and Johan Angergård (Acid House Kings, Poprace). They made simple bedroom recordings of their three first songs and sent them to their ten favourite labels. The response was just as immediate as it was good with half of the labels wanting to release the band. Club 8 chose the Spanish label Siesta where they released their debut single »Me too« later the same year and the debut album »Nouvelle« the year after..\r\n\r\nThe sound on the debut album was definitely a bit naive and twee. And as charming as a lot of people found the debut the follow up »The friend I once had« (1998) felt like a big step forward for the band. Their mix of bossa nova, glittery guitars, shiny pop melodies and small hints of dance music made this album an indie-success. They also debuted as a live act with a performance at CMJ in New York in 1999.\r\n\r\nStriving for constant change and improvements Club 8 moved away from the bossa nova influences and direct pop songs of »The friend I once had« with the self-titled follow up. »Club 8« (2001-Parasol/Labrador/Flavour of Sound) was both darker and slower. Still, they managed to expand their audience and had somewhat of a hit with »Love in december«. The only real problem the band had experienced was the fact that recording on limited studio time was a hindrance to their experimental lusts. Late 2001 Club 8, along with fellow band Acid House Kings, set up their own recording studio – Summersound Studios.\r\n\r\nWith 24/7 access to a recording studio of their own Club 8 enterered their most creative and productive phase to date recording the diversified, semi-electronic and slightly experimental, but intensly emotional »Spring came, rain fell« in 2002 (Parasol/Labrador/Dodgie Disc) and the more guitar-based and kept together follow up »Strangely beautiful« (2003-Parasol/Labrador/Quince). The latter contained the song »Saturday night engine« which was, very accuately, described as " a storming (very) Northern soul-inspired track bursting with an excitement that sounded quite out of place in that quiet group''s discography” and a forerunner to Johan’s band The Legends according to All Music.\r\n\r\nAfter the release of »Strangely beautiful« Club 8’s activity slowed down while Johan formed The Legends and released three albums with the band between 2003 and 2006, plus the album ”Sing along with Acid House Kings” with Acid House Kings in 2005. During this period Club 8 only did a few minor tours in Asia and Europe.\r\n\r\nSummer 2006 Club 8 was about to burst of creativity and urge to start recording again and in September they started recording their 6th album.\r\n\r\n»The boy who couldn’t stop dreaming« is Club 8s most profound to date, balancing perfectly between sunshine and melancholia. Twelve songs that’ll make you sing along about death to while dreaming of summer days. A glorious return to say the least.'),
(6250, 'Airliner', 'http://www.indievox.com/airliner', 'http://cdn-data.indievox.com/indievox_user/30000/6250/pix/6250180X180.jpg?1427770883', 3, 'Airliner大型客機樂團，Swedish-Pop樂團Aerospace成員Kristian Rosegren化身一人樂團。\r\nAirliner is a one man project by Kristian Rosengren, former guitarist of Aerospace. He''s been writing beautiful and slow pop songs for years and his debut came out in 1999. It was split 7" single on Labrador Records. A single which sold out quickly and gained a very good reputation among the pop loving kids around the world.\r\n\r\nIn the spring of 2002 Airliner felt ready to start recording his debut album and Johan Angergård of Club 8 and Acid House Kings was hired to record and produce the album in the famous Summersound Studios. The album, "The last days of August" was released in February 2003. Ten sad and wonderfully sensitive pop songs about love and lost.\r\n\r\nAirliner is right now building his own studio in the comfort of his home. Will this result in a new album? Only time can tell.'),
(6253, 'Irene', 'http://www.indievox.com/irene', 'http://cdn3-data.indievox.com/indievox_user/30000/6253/pix/6253180X180.jpg?1427770883', 2, 'Irene 艾琳樂團，瑞典清新指標品牌Labrador繼Sambassadeur、Ronderlin後又一令人驚艷的瑞典哥登堡新團，多人編制下形成了樂器和人聲的豐富性，從而令樂團本質有了更多樣繁瑣的隨意編排，又不失其簡單清新的迷人特性。\r\n每一首歌曲皆歌頌著愛情/海灘/星星/夏天，同時以一次完成的即興錄音方式，製出了洋溢美國西岸的吉他歡愉，還有靈魂合聲樂團的節奏感，比幾年前出現過的The Thrills多了些Indie-Pop的可愛俏皮。\r\nIrene grew into a full scale band quite spontaneously in 2005. The members are all friends from the local pub in Göteborg, Sweden. Some songs that Tobias Isaksson (aka Bobby) had written just couldn''t wait to be performed live. The people that did the first show had so much fun that they wanted to stick around. By the autumn of 2005 Irene was an octet with semi-permanent members. Shortly after that the record label Labrador signed the band.\r\n\r\nA critically acclaimed debut album called Apple Bay was released in 2006. It was an upbeat, super-short, 24 minute tribute to the 60''s sound with most instruments recorded live. Apple Bay has been licensed in The USA, Australia, Thailand and Taiwan and distributed via Labrador''s associates in countries all over the world. In the spring 2007 tours of England, France, Spain and Germany made Irene aspire to take their music to a new level. The result was an almost perfectly executed, timeless pop trip of 27 minutes titled Long Gone Since Last Summer. Although the album is due in Sweden less than one year after the debut it displays a band with brand new qualities. The members of Irene remain beach crooners, lounge punks and next door nice guys.'),
(6255, 'janckerchen', 'http://www.indievox.com/janckerchen', 'http://cdn1-data.indievox.com/indievox_user/30000/6255/pix/6255180X180.png?1427770883', 0, ''),
(6293, 'Corduroy Utd.', 'http://www.indievox.com/corduroyutd', 'http://cdn-data.indievox.com/indievox_user/30000/6293/pix/6293180X180.jpg?1427770884', 3, 'Corduroy Utd. 燈芯絨樂團，2002年EP作品Behine My Back獲香港mcb音樂殖民地雙週刊選為全年最佳單曲之一，經過新團員的加入和兩年時間的磨練，樂團親自參與製作的首張專輯Oh Eira正式發表。\r\n呈現的是一種60年代車庫流行氣息、英式吉他的搖擺，還有屬於它們自己的無畏開心味道，聽來確實能讓人無憂開懷，骨子裡的幼稚童真無疑是年輕才擁有的專利。\r\nOnce in a while you get bored. Perhaps you then go out for a drink or two. Perhaps you even end up completely shit-faced. And here is where you might form a band. It’s quite easy, when you’re lying there passed out on the dance floor, a couple of merciful souls are bound to pick you up and carry you home. This is when you might ask these merciful souls whether they would want to play in your band. The souls will most likely tell you that of course they would like to, but they’ve got a lot on with their other bands at the time. This is when you pull out the ace from your sleeve and tell them that you’ve got a record deal and you’ve got yourself a band!.\r\n\r\nNow, what might this band be playing then? Well, when you take one lead singer, who as a former swimmer, has the lung capacity to wail your ears to the other side of the Atlantic ocean, a bass player who has a past as a basketball player playing along with famous Swedish hip-hop acts, a guitarist with a past as a hockeyplayer alongside Swedish all-stars like Sebastian Wik, a trumpet player who used to enjoy beating the crap out of her, now late, grandmother in badminton (may the lord have mercy on her soul), a guitar and trombone player taken straight out of the defence of the football team Lokomotiv Neger, a skateboarding organist with constantly broken hands, ribs and wrists and a drummer who has no connection with sports at all it ends up sounding more or less like Hefner running into a high-pitched Morrissey on the jogging course.\r\n\r\nBut you must not be led to think that this energy package has only received its glory through deeds connected to sport. These fine youngsters are already something of veterans on the underground pop scene of Stockholm. Emerging from groups like, GHB, The Crew, Bristol Ltd., The Outbreak, Regor, The Fermats, The Protection Rooms, Gadfic Moore, The Shattered Charlies, Fabulous Combo, Mornel, The Cuff and Jaap Stam this is something of an underground supergroup. So get into your best party frock and allow your dancing body to fall into the depths of Stockholm’s finest ntilounge.'),
(6295, 'Edson', 'http://www.indievox.com/edson', 'http://cdn-data.indievox.com/indievox_user/30000/6295/pix/6295180X180.jpg?1427770884', 4, 'Edson was formed by Pelle Carlberg in the summer of 1998, and he named the band after the great soccer player Edson Arantes do Nascimento, i.e. Pelé. The first couple of months the piano took a prominent part in the sound, giving the songs a tangible jazz pop flavour. Initially the band was Pelle''s solo project, but since then it has more and more developed into a democratic unity, with Pelle as the songwriter and lead singer.\r\n\r\nIn december of 1999 the band got the formation it has today: Pelle sings, Filip Carvell plays the acoustic and the electric guitar and sings, Helena Söderman plays the flute, melodica, harmonica, glockenspiel, Wurlitzer and sings, Mårten Josjö plays the electric guitar, Mats Deltin plays the bass and Ulf Lundberg the drums.\r\n\r\nIn 1999 Edson made about 30 live appearances, e.g. one at the demo stage of the Hultsfred festival in Sweden. After the performance Edson met John Cloud, who was interested in releasing something on his label Stormstreet records. In September a four-track EP was released containing the songs »Sunday, loverly sunday«, »I Didn´t Mean to be Mean«, »22:22 {We Need a Quarrel, We Need a Fight}« and »Terry Whips«.\r\n\r\nThe same year the band contributed with two songs on the compilation CD »The Sound of Young Sweden« and with one song each on Sound Affects Magazine''s »Hultsfred special-CD« and the »Demoscenen«-CD of the Hultsfred festival. The »Sunday, lovely sunday« EP was also released by Matinée Recordings in the US, but with a slightly different tracklist.\r\n\r\nIn the autumn of -00 Edson was signed to Summersound Recordings and recorded their debut album »Unwind with edson«, which was released February 14 2001 and was received well.\r\n\r\nAlbum number two, »For Strength«, was recorded and mixed during ten intensive days in the end of December of 2001, once again with Andreas Ahlenius as technician and once again mainly in the rock metropolis of Gävle, Sweden. The result is very satisfactory. Edson has evolved as a unity, and their sound is more homogenous and personal.'),
(6297, 'Acid House Kings', 'http://www.indievox.com/acidhousekings', 'http://cdn1-data.indievox.com/indievox_user/30000/6297/pix/6297180X180.jpg?1427770884', 15, 'Acid House Kings 迷幻小屋樂團，Swedish-Pop之音/純情清新樂派長青必備經典終於正式在台發行!!!\r\n清爽愉快的吉他聲音，笨笨的鼓機敲打，稚嫩天真的年輕嗓音，沒辦法包容太多憂愁的歌詞，永不嫌多的陽光，再加上刻骨銘心的甜蜜初戀，Acid House Kings這三個字就這樣從此擄獲所有Indie-Pop樂迷的心。\r\n超過10年的組成歷史，以及團員身兼Club 8、Starlet等樂團身份，讓Acid House Kings不僅是瑞典清新音樂最典範的代表，其自組廠牌Labrador Records和Summersound錄音室，更是孕育瑞典新世代樂團的搖籃 。'),
(6333, '1724 Records', 'http://www.indievox.com/1724', 'http://cdn3-data.indievox.com/indievox_user/30000/6333/pix/6333180X180.jpg?1427770885', 47, '　　位於中國北京的拾柒貳肆唱片是壹家專註於獨立音樂聲景傳播的微型唱片廠牌，成立於2006年6月。\n　　拾柒貳肆這個名字來自如下理念：年輕時的感同身受將影響妳壹生的軌跡。而音樂擁有改變個體心靈形狀的力量。\n　　拾柒貳肆的出品和行動也大抵秉承如上標準。　\n　　拾柒貳肆合作藝人包括48V、拇指姑娘、oNEwAY、kayak、pentatonic、梁奕源、時過夏末、琥珀、深綠海、文雀、saisa（日本）、鄧永鵬。'),
(6339, '四分衛', 'http://www.indievox.com/backquarter', 'http://cdn3-data.indievox.com/indievox_user/30000/6339/pix/6339180X180.jpg?1427770885', 443, '四分衛-Quarterback\n \n \n\n關於「四分衛」-「Quarterback」\n\n台灣搖滾史上從不缺席的樂團－四分衛\n93年成軍　歷經多次成員變更，就和許多樂團一樣，一開始四分衛也從演唱經典西洋搖滾歌出發，後來才開始慢慢累積自己的創作， 一步步建立起屬於四分衛獨有的樂風。\n多年來  四分衛維持著不討好、不妥協的硬式搖滾性格。\n歷經多年翻滾，在台灣樂團環境裡，更是找出一種獨一無二的生存方式。\n參與過許多的演出後，依舊奔馳在這片遼闊音樂球場上，充分反應了美式足球中的重要角色。\n\n玩團就是應該要開開心心的玩\n團長虎神哥說過：『玩團最基本就是玩的開心。』\n我們在四分衛身上看到的，卻無關乎年紀，而是一種純粹。\n純粹的支持他們十幾年，走過這條稱不上順遂、內外在卻都有著考驗的道路。\n單純、簡單的享受的音樂，說說笑笑、胡鬧開玩笑。\n當手中拿起樂器、踏上舞台，四分衛讓每件事情都變得有趣起來，這就是他們玩團之道。\n就從下一首旋律開始…你該聽聽四分衛的歌\n\n團員及職稱\n主唱兼吉他  阿山  陳如山\n吉他兼團長  虎神  鄭峰昇 \n貝斯        奧迪  林弘毅 \n鼓手        緯緯  王誌緯\n四分衛紀事：\n成立於1995年（前身[[Hexagon六角形]]於1993年成立）\n* 1993年3月四分衛成立。\n* 1994年於SCUM(當時有地下樂團演出的PUB)開始演出。 \n* 1998年同年四分衛首張專輯『起來』進入錄製階段。參加第二屆『春天吶喊』演出,並收錄「活著」在『牛年吶喊』 專輯(友善的狗發行)。 \n* 1999年首張專輯『起來』角頭音樂九月發行。\n* 2000年4月以『起來』專輯入圍第11屆金曲獎最佳樂團提名，同年入圍的樂團還包括有亂彈、脫拉庫、花兒、五月天獲金曲獎最佳樂團提名。 \n*2000年加入動能唱片。\n*2001年8月限量EP『 Pure Rock 』。\n*2001年9月第二張專輯『 Deep Blue 』發行。\n*2002年1月獲得CHANNEL「V」的「華語榜中榜」「特別推薦新浪潮樂團」獎，＠北京。\n*2002年3月入圍第13屆金曲獎『最佳樂團獎』提名,同時入圍的還有五月天、刺客、交工樂隊。\n*2002年10月獲邀香港『華人音樂搖滾演唱會』台灣代表團 \n*2003年7月成軍十年  第三張專輯『 ROCK TEAM 』發行 \n*2004年4月『 ROCK TEAM 』專輯入圍第15屆金曲獎最佳樂團提名。同\n年入圍的樂團還包括有Tizzy Bac、信樂團、波賓樂團、五月天 獲金曲獎最佳樂團提名。\n*2005年6月發行概念性單曲三張『 R.G.B 』。\n*2005年8月第四張專輯 『 W 』 發行。\n*2005年10月亞洲流行音樂節演出＠東京。\n*2006年7月國際貢寮海洋音樂祭演出團體。\n*2007年2月單曲『 夜行軍 』 限量發行。\n*2008年4月春天吶喊演出。\n*2008年8月第五張專輯『 WORLD 』發行。\n*2008年9月四分衛 Endless演唱會。\n*2012年3月Legacy Live house 十再好九不見-19週年演唱會。\n*2012年8月日本SummerSonic音樂節演出\n*2012年8月團團團團團with 五月天、亂彈阿翔、脫拉褲、董事長 ＠小巨蛋演出。\n*2012年10月大彩虹音樂節＠高雄。\n*2012年10月Mini concert＠西門河岸留言。\n*2013年5月草莓音樂節＠上海。\n*2013年9月一起來、二十年、山迪追虎、四分衛，演唱會＠ATT SHOWBOX。\n*2013年9月四分衛 第六張專輯 『 愛可以讓我們在一起 』發行。\n*2013年10月四分衛、脫拉庫中國巡演＠上海、杭州、北京、武漢、廣州、深圳、香港、惠洲、成都、重慶。\n*2014年 電影：一首搖滾上月球 主題曲。獲得金馬獎最佳電影主題曲。\n*2014年 搖滾辦桌演出。\n*2014年 新加坡MUSIC MATTERS演出\n*2014年 金音獎 最佳搖滾單曲、最佳搖滾樂團\n*2015年1月 四分衛 EP『 大人小孩 』發行。\n\n發行音樂專輯：\n《赤聲搖滾(1)》，1997年。\n《ㄞ國歌曲》，1997年12月。\n《牛年春天吶喊(1)》，1998年。 \n《起來》，1999年8月。\n《眾藝-SUPER》，2000年5月。\n《四分衛EP》，2001年8月。\n《Deep Blue》，2001年9月。\n《Deep Blue (全新改版)》，2001年10月。\n《ROCK TEAM》，2002年。\n《R/G/B》，2005年。\n《W》，2005年。\n《World》，2008年。\n《愛可以讓我們在一起》，2013年。\n《大人小孩》，2015年。\n\n\n'),
(6344, 'Amanda McBroom', 'http://www.indievox.com/amandamcbroom', 'http://cdn1-data.indievox.com/indievox_user/30000/6344/pix/6344180X180.jpg?1427770885', 0, 'This Los Angeles-based songwriter and cabaret singer is probably best known for her song "The Rose," a hit in 1979 for Bette Midler. McBroom has also appeared on stage in "Jacques Brel Is Alive and Well" and "See Saw," and also tours regularly. Her debut album, Growing Up in Hollywood with Lincoln Mayorga, was a best-seller for the prestigious Sheffield Labs label, as was her followup, West of Oz.'),
(6348, 'Kelly Sweet', 'http://www.indievox.com/kellysweet', 'http://cdn3-data.indievox.com/indievox_user/30000/6348/pix/6348180X180.jpg?1427770885', 4, 'Soft-voiced pop vocalist Kelly Sweet was born into a creative and musical family. In their home in Cape Cod, MA, she was raised by her father, a jazz pianist, and her artist mother. Learning to play notes on the piano before she could walk, Sweet sang live for an audience for the first time at age four at the Cape Cod Conservatory. After her parents divorced, she and her mother moved to Utah, where she began working harder honing her craft. Around age 14, Sweet and her mother rented out their home in Utah and began touring the western United States for two years, working to get Sweet her touring wings, as well as to get her name out. The hard work paid off and she ended up opening for Kenny Loggins in Las Vegas, and also sang the national anthem three different times before L.A. Lakers NBA games. She met up with producer, arranger, and songwriter Mark Portmann (Celine Dion) in the summer of 2004. The two began writing songs together, resulting in the turning point of her career into a professional musician, and she was eventually signed to Razor &amp; Tie Records. Sweet''s debut, We Are One, surfaced in March 2007. '),
(6375, 'Leslies', 'http://www.indievox.com/leslies', 'http://cdn-data.indievox.com/indievox_user/30000/6375/pix/6375180X180.jpg?1427770886', 1, 'Leslies 萊斯利樂團，崛起於九十年代中期的五人Swedish-Pop中堅樂團。以主唱Martin Berndtsson為首、成軍於1993年的Leslies，獲譽為The Cardigans、Eggstone的綜合體，而這張睽違多年的第三張專輯交由知名瑞典樂團The Mopeds操刀製作。\r\n保有一貫流暢的Swedish-Pop特質之餘，還流露出源自於八十年代Jangle-Pop、九十年代Britpop薰陶的爽朗陽光氣息。\r\nThis is guitar driven pop with a twist. Leslies make the songs simple if they need to be simple, and complex if that''s what the songs need, but they never spare anything when it comes to arrangements. Vibraphone, brass and piano contribute to their catchy songs in a wonderful way.\r\n\r\nOn this, their third album, Leslies return to the Tambourine Studios in Malmö. This time produced by the Mopeds. Their first album was full of glittery pop songs and jangly guitars. Their second album found the jangly sounds replaced by a more distorted ones and a more mature sound. On this third album their somewhere in between the both. This is definitely their best album to date.\r\n\r\nThink Cardigans, Lloyd Cole and Strokes and you know what we''re talking about.'),
(6377, 'Lydia Gray', 'http://www.indievox.com/lydiagray', 'http://cdn2-data.indievox.com/indievox_user/30000/6377/pix/6377180X180.jpg?1427770886', 11, '60~90年代是流行音樂最閃耀的時光，我們得以聆聽Beatles、Genesis、Crowded House、Shawn Colvin、Elton John膾炙人口的作品陪伴我們渡過悠悠時光。時光荏然，來自美國的Lydia Gray承襲其母親－爵士名伶Betty Johnson－的音樂細胞，與生俱來的完美音感與穿透力十足、媲美民謠詩人Janis Ian的通透嗓音；在低迷徬徨的今日，又再次以清爽的音樂與嗓音溫潤我們的耳朵。簡單的樂器編制搭配Lydia芳醇的vocal，譜出那隱含於音樂之內感染力滿懷的情意結。正如Lydia之於此張錄音表白：「專輯的每首歌都可能是你生命中某些時候的主題曲。」此碟淬選經典樂隊Beatles靈魂 Lennon與McCartney所譜寫之For No One、And I Love Him，搖滾名團Genesis之昔日主腦Peter Gabriel雋永金曲In Your Eyes，20世紀最佳作曲家Burt Bacharach全球暢銷單曲Look of Love，經典樂隊Crowded House靈魂人物Niel Finn的傳唱佳謠Better Be Home Soon。聽著此碟傳來心曠神怡的樂音，腦中浮現智利詩人聶魯達 (Pablo Neruda)之詩－「I came here to sing, and for you to sing with me.」恰巧呈現此碟神髓。'),
(6378, 'Noon', 'http://www.indievox.com/noon', 'http://cdn1-data.indievox.com/indievox_user/30000/6378/pix/6378180X180.jpg?1427770886', 44, '「似是來自於天真小孩般的吟唱，似水一樣的舒展性與存在感」。這是日本樂界給予這位年輕甜美的女聲的讚美。出生於大阪，祖國是韓國的日韓混血美女NOON，2003年於日本出道即獲得樂界與市場高度的評價與銷售；獨特的嗓音兩度被收錄在以發燒選曲聞名的「Best Audiophile Voice」系列。在台灣以第2張專輯「晴空下的童話My Fairy Tale」初探市場的NOON，也受到各大電台DJ與 樂迷的熱烈迴響。 '),
(6381, 'Sambassadeur', 'http://www.indievox.com/sambassadeur', 'http://cdn2-data.indievox.com/indievox_user/30000/6381/pix/6381180X180.jpg?1427770886', 14, 'Sambassadeur 使節樂團，這個連英國XFM和BBC電台也強力放送的瑞典新秀樂團，延續著以The Radio Dept.為首、結合傳統瑞典清新和JAMC/My Bloody Valentine式白色噪音基因的新獨特樂型，同時吸納The Go Betweens、France Gall、The Velvet Underground、Pavement的影響而來。\r\n首張同名專輯裡得見男女主唱Daniel與Anna交織出樂團迴然不同的性格，但盪出的卻是相同光線下的連綿溫柔，還滲許些朦朧夢幻。英國獨立音樂網站Drowned In Sound四顆星高評價肯定。\r\n\r\nSambassadeur debuted on Labrador in winter 2005 with the release of the "Between the Lines"-EP. The EP was followed by their self titled debut album later that year. The songs were all recorded at home which gave the production a primitive quality that labled them by some as being a lo-fi-twee act. This was never the bands intention.\r\n\r\nIf the cliché is that songs are like children, then Sambassadeur saw no purpose in stagnating in front of their home-computer while watching their kids being taken custody by those who didn''t have the ability to, indeed, read between the lines and see through the understated surface of the songs. This called for some change.\r\n\r\nThe Ep "Coastal Affairs", relased in may 2006, marked the start of a development towards a more luxurious setting. Without loosing their enigmatic qualities, songs like "Kate" and "Marie" introduced a breeze of new confidence. The Sambassadeurs saw the oportunity to take things to even greater hights and returned to the scene in late august 2007 with "Subtle Changes". The first single of the upcoming album "Migration" and also the first Sambassadeur-song to feature a saxophone.\r\n\r\nThree words to get you started on "Migration": Melodies, bitterness and some minor thievery. Now it''s up to you to listen, draw your own conclusions and misinterpret. Have fun! '),
(6385, '夏生', 'http://www.indievox.com/summerbred', 'http://cdn2-data.indievox.com/indievox_user/30000/6385/pix/6385180X180.jpg?1427770886', 74, '沒有電吉他的。搖。滾。樂。\r\n2008 最新單曲「I Wanna be Your Johnny Depp」，收錄在《大趴踢》搖滾電音雙 CD 合輯當中，Come with Us 創意團隊統籌發行。'),
(6386, 'The Radio Dept. ', 'http://www.indievox.com/theradiodept', 'http://cdn3-data.indievox.com/indievox_user/30000/6386/pix/6386180X180.jpg?1427770886', 54, 'The Radio Dept 無線電站樂團，The Radio Dept在1995年由還在學校的好夥伴Elin Almered和Johan Duncanson組成，其後Johan和Martin Larsson彈彈奏奏寫寫歌，等到所有陸續加入團員一起真正像個樂團排練已是2001年，包括了彈貝斯的Lisa Carlberg、和打鼓的Per Blomgren。經由Sonic雜誌附贈CD上的樂團作品，從而獲得Labrador Records賞識簽入旗下。The Radio Dept音樂最特別吸引人的，莫過於吉他效果的運用，還有鼓聲環境一起塑造出低傳又夢幻的音質美感，但也不能簡單歸於90年代初噪音流行吉他類型分類，別忘了The Radio Dept的骨子裡流著是瑞典吉他音樂的清新血液。\r\nThe Radio Dept. was formed by Elin Almered and Johan Duncanson in 1995 who were in the school together in their early teenage. The name was taken from a gas station/radio repairer in Lund {Sweden} which had a large sign with the name »Radioavdelningen« {The Radio Department in Swedish...} hanging outside their shop. Just like today Elin and Johan hung out with people who, if they didn''t play music, were into photo, film, art and the likes. The Radio Deptartment was a suiting name as it became a department of it''s own among their friends'' activities.\r\n\r\nSince 1995 members has been coming and going and at some points there has never really been a Radio Department at all. Martin Larsson and Johan Duncanson started playing together in 1998 and decided to use the name The Radio Dept. Since then the band has done lots of gigs and lots recordings. The Radio Dept. has recorded on 4-tracks in friends'' living rooms or at home, in smelly wharehouse, in demo studios with blinking fluorecent lightning and at schools.\r\n\r\nIn the autumn of 2001 Lisa Carlberg, bass player and the love of Martin, and Per Blomgren, drums, joined the band and they started rehearsing in the way bands so often do. The latest recordings were sent to the music magazine Sonic and got a nice review. They were also on the free CD sampler that comes with the magazine. That''s when Labrador Records discovered and signed the band.\r\n\r\nTheir debut album "Lesser Matters" which was released in the spring of 2003 was an underground success internationally and Labrador''s first entrance in the sales charts in Sweden. The buzz that slowly grew to give the band worldwide recognition with a little help from XL Recordings who released the album in large parts of the world, and the release of Sofia Coppola''s Marie Antoinette, which featured "Keen on Boys, [from "Lesser matters]" "Pulling Our Weight, [from the EP with the same name, 2004]" and "I Don''t Like It Like This. [from the EP "This past week", 2005]"\r\n\r\nTheir highly anticipated second album, "Pet grief", was released in the spring of 2006 and showed a slightly more dreamy, and less noisy, side of the band. The album reached #11 in the Swedish charts and continued to give the band new fans all over the world.\r\n\r\nIn the beginning of 2007 people started talking about new material from The Radio Dept. There was even a rumour going on that they were working on two albums simultaneously and that both would be released in May the same year. In other words; two albums merely one year after the release of the previous album ”Pet Grief”. Those who had followed the band for a few years and know how they work probably suspected this would not happen.\r\nThe single "Freddie and the Trojan Horse" was released in May 2008 and it''s a first taste of their upcoming album ”Clinging to a scheme” due to be released in the fall/winter of 2008. The new songs are said to be influenced by minimalistic post-punk, krautrock, repetitive "motorik" beat and ambient noise.'),
(6387, 'Tribeca', 'http://www.indievox.com/tribeca', 'http://cdn2-data.indievox.com/indievox_user/30000/6387/pix/6387180X180.jpg?1427770886', 13, 'Tribeca 曼哈頓三角二人組，將英式搖滾憂鬱融入浪漫Synth-Pop電音的完美平衡。主音歌手Lasse Lindh介於Conor Oberst(Bright Eyes主唱)之孤獨脆弱和Brett Anderson(Suede)之妖媚纖細的唱腔，帶出一首首穿梭於Synth-Pop、Indie-Pop、Trip-Hop間的沉醉樂章，讓吉他、鍵琴與鼓奏朦朧交錯出難以抗拒的電氣溫柔。Musicscan網站8/10分高評價肯定。\r\nTribeca is the band of Lasse Lindh and Claes Björklund. The band was formed with one purpose in mind: To make music we loved but never heard anywhere. In other words: Tribeca was spawned by rage. Sick and tired of bands doing it all wrong the only way out was to do it themselves. Sounds pretentious? Well, why not..\r\n\r\nThe Tribeca saga started a chill winter evening at a cafe in Stockholm, Sweden when singer/songwriter Lasse Lindh, invited his favorite producer, Claes Björklund {who produced Lasse Lindh''s »You wake up at sea tac«}, over for a cup of coffee. The two held the same musical ideas and ideals and that marked the start for Tribeca.\r\n\r\nShortly after Tribeca headed for the country for four months where they recorded what turned out to be »Kate -97«, their debut album. A long time for recording an album you might say, but Claes isn’t exactly the sloppy kind of producer. Tribeca recorded and mixed for about four months. And you can really hear that on the album, it''s a lot of very great sounds that’s isn’t made in an instance..\r\n\r\nTribeca »Kate -97« was released in August 2002 on Labrador Records, Mushroom Pillow {Spain} and Philter {Japan}.\r\n\r\nLate summer 2002 Lasse Lindh entered the studio with producer Claes Björklund again. This time to record a new Lasse Lindh album. The idea was to record most stuff live in the studio and end up an album based on live takes with a rough, guitar based sound.\r\n\r\nAutumn 2003: Lasse Lindh shows up at the Labrador office with the finished material: An all together electronic pop album by Tribeca. “Dragon Down” contains twelve highly a ddictive pop songs in crystal clear production with analogue synthezisers, groovy old school beats, and singer Lasse''s smooth vocals up in the front. A truly wonderful album indeed! '),
(6390, 'Ronderlin', 'http://www.indievox.com/ronderlin', 'http://cdn1-data.indievox.com/indievox_user/30000/6390/pix/6390180X180.jpg?1427770886', 1, 'Ronderlin 朗德琳樂團，不知道被北歐的陽光灑射是何樣感覺，但聽了Ronderlin的歌曲，叫人想閉起雙眼，只覺一股煦陽輕撫耳旁，吉他撩撥，鼓棒輕敲，偶有琴鍵和鳴，說是有多愜意舒懶，絕不為過。\r\nRonderlin一行6人，成軍於1998年，此張專輯Wave Another Day Goodbye是他們的第一張，大部份詞曲皆由主唱Karl-Johan Grahm，這位柔情漢子一手包辦，其他成員包括了貝斯Styrbjorn Ekman、吉他兼歌唱Johan Lindwall、鼓手Tommy Dannefjord、風琴、鋼琴、法國號Per larsson以及吉他Mats Lundquist。陣容雖然陌生，但音樂卻來得親切，憑著就是Ronderlin真摰純情的樂聲。\r\n\r\nIn the mid 90th Karl-Johan, Styrbjorn and Johan moved from Eksjo, a small town in Smaland, to Gothenburg in order to form a new band. A few months later Tommy joined them and during the next year so did Per and Mats. In 1998 Ronderlin was formed.'),
(6424, '先知瑪莉', 'http://www.indievox.com/maryseethefuture', 'http://cdn1-data.indievox.com/indievox_user/30000/6424/pix/6424180X180.jpg?1427770887', 1416, 'Mary See the Future 於2007年初組成，以台北為中心活動，發行過兩張單曲，曲風以英式搖滾為基底，融合古典樂的聲響結構，音樂在暴躁狂熱與陰鬱優雅的兩種面相中反差著。\n\n2010年初於The Next Big Thing「見證大團」系列活動嶄露頭角後，率續參與了廈門海峽搖滾音樂節、沖繩國際亞洲音樂節，並擔任黃貫中台北演唱會開場演出、Placebo 台北演唱會開場樂團。今年至英國利物浦參與Liverpool SoundCity音樂節期間，更受邀BBC電台接受專訪。\n\n關於團名的來由似乎是必考題，事實上就像Josh所說，Mary是英語系社會中常見的名字，代表著樂團裡這三位平凡到不行的我們。只不過，我們透過了某種方式找到了往未來前進的力量，這個方式或許就是創作與摸索。'),
(6474, 'El Perro Del Mar', 'http://www.indievox.com/elperrodelmar', 'http://cdn3-data.indievox.com/indievox_user/30000/6474/pix/6474180X180.jpg?1427770888', 1, 'El Perro del Mar was founded in the end of 2003 around the idea and need\r\nof making music on terms of one''s own. Behind the alter-ego is the sole member Sarah Assbring.\r\nEl Perro del Mar started out as what is often referred to as an mp3-artist and in spring 2004 the first cdr-ep ''Baby, I''ve been in a bad place'' was released by the then newly started Swedish label Hybris. Two more cdr-ep:s, ''I''ve got good news'' and ''Holiday Special'', were released shortly thereafter.\r\nIn late 2004 the first official ep ''What''s new? El Perro del Mar'' was released, including the songs ''I can''t talk about it'', ''This Loneliness'' and ''It''s all good''. Also around this time, she contributed with the song ''Shake it off'' on a joint and very limited split single initiated by friend Jens Lekman. She joined him shortly thereafter as opening act on his tour in Sweden.\r\nIn May 2005 all the previous unofficial and official releases were gathered to form the compilation album ''Look! It''s El Perro del Mar!''. Later that year the ep ''God Knows (You Gotta Give to Get) was released, including the songs ''God Knows'', ''Do the Dog'' and ''Say''.\r\nDuring spring 2006 a slightly updated version of the debut album was released in England and in Europe by British label Memphis Industries.\r\nBy the end of 2006 the self-titled album was released in the U.S. as well as in Australia and New Zealand. The album received rave reviews.\r\nEl Perro del Mar also had the opportunity to make a short and successful tour in Brazil. In spring 2007 El Perro del Mar toured the U.S.\r\n\r\nEl Perro del Mar left the label Hybris and found a new home on Licking Fingers, the Concretes own label. It was time for new ideas and new ways.\r\nAnd so during the spring and summer of 2007 the much longed-for work on the second album ''From the Valley to the Stars'' began. The recordings as well as the producing were done by El Perro del Mar herself in her studio in Gothenburg. With the exception of a trip around India in the fall the intense work on the album lasted until December 2007.\r\nThe album was released in Scandinavia in February. It was preceded by the release of the single ''How Did We Forget?''.\r\nIn the U.S. ''From the Valley to the Stars'' was released on April 22nd. In May the release was followed by a North American tour together with Swedish fellows Lykke Li and Anna Ternheim.'),
(6476, 'Wan Light', 'http://www.indievox.com/wanlight', 'http://cdn3-data.indievox.com/indievox_user/30000/6476/pix/6476180X180.jpg?1427770888', 6, 'Wan Light 微光樂團，以八十年代格拉斯哥New Wave名團Orange Juice 同名作品所命名，2002年成軍之斯德哥爾摩雙人樂團獲清新名廠Labrador網羅後，交由瑞典知名製作人Björn Öqvist操刀的首張專輯。以孤寂的鋼琴琴音與簡約的民謠吉他掃撥為主軸，梅花竹間點綴的電子聲效與迷幻吉他音牆，巧妙地強化了作品的復古與傷感情緒，被形容為Mercury Rev、Neil Young、Flaming Lips乃至Pet Shop Boys的綜合體。\r\n\r\nWan Light from Stockholm is K. Svensson and M. Karnock. The band is named after an old Orange Juice song, but that''s all they have in common with Edwyn Collin''s old band. Wan Light''s music are based on traditional singer/songwriter songs, often electronically produced, but sometimes they choose a more minimalistic production with just a lonely piano.\r\n\r\nThe lyrics are multifaceted and easy in the contours, still very vivid. Listening to the music of Wan Light evokes a great deal of pictures. Their music can be described as beautiful and experimental pop with a big distance to rock and harshness.\r\n\r\nThe two members of Wan Light have been playing together for a long time, as drummer and bass player respectively. When they by coincidence changed their direction as musicians in the year 2002 they found something that resulted in a close collaboration with producer Björn Öqvist.\r\n\r\nThe album »Let''s wake up somewhere else« offers a 40 minutes long journey with wide range of experiences on the way. It contains the two singles »Get it Straighter« and »Landmarks and Houses«.\r\n\r\nLet us all wake up somewhere else... preferably in Wan Light''s land.'),
(6477, 'Laurel Music', 'http://www.indievox.com/laurelmusic', 'http://cdn2-data.indievox.com/indievox_user/30000/6477/pix/6477180X180.jpg?1427770888', 4, 'Tobias Isaksson had been writing songs for ten years and for a few years his\r\nsinger/songwriter project had been figuring in magazines such as Sound Affects and Sonic. But it was when Labrador presented him with Douglas Heart’s super vocalist Malin Dahlberg late in 2001 that his ship finally came in.\r\n\r\nShe liked his sense for melodies and they were asked to record some songs for »The Sound Of Young Sweden, vol. 3«. Once their correspondence started a close relationship was rapidly developed and soon Laurel Music was a dynamic duo. The combination of his timeless qualities as a songwriter akin to Neil Young, Morrissey/Marr and Tim Hardin and her ethereal vocals inspired by soft emo pop like Geoff Farina, The Secret Stars and Ida made their musical collaboration quite rare.\r\n\r\nAt first, when their rehearsal sessions took place in his living room, they often ended up giggling and listening to too many records. But as they entered the studio to record their debut album, they realised they needed a full band to complete the sound. Top drummer Max Sjöholm (Douglas Heart, Afraid Of Stairs) joined them as a permanent member and Tobias played just about every instrument he could get hold of. Finally some friends assisted with whatever the three weren’t able to do.\r\n\r\nTo this day, the permanent members remain Tobias, Malin and Max, but on stage Laurel Music is a musical collective that can appear as anything from a duo to a sextet. Expect a soft, melancholic masterpiece and some\r\nheartwarming live shows in the future!'),
(6478, 'Suburban Kids With Biblical Names', 'http://www.indievox.com/suburbankidswithbiblicalnames', 'http://cdn3-data.indievox.com/indievox_user/30000/6478/pix/6478180X180.jpg?1427770888', 0, 'Suburban Kids With Biblical Names 聖名市郊小子樂團，這個樹立不做作純真風格的Labrador新進二人樂團，與瑞典當代一些民謠歌手如El Perro Del Mar、Jens Lekman等分庭抗禮。首張專輯確然是結合美國低傳真與清新民謠的典範之作，除了擅用50/60年代的討喜合聲外，唱腔還帶有Stephin Merrit的低沉特色，以及Darren Hayman的漫不經心。\r\n\r\nSuburban Kids with Biblical Names wants to ”turn all the dance floors into a burnings inferno of Ba-ba-ba” to quote the Kids themselves. And with their debut single “Rent a wreck”, they surely did.\r\n\r\nThey’ve only existed since December 2003, still they Already sound as if they’ve been writing songs together since the beginning of time. Or perhaps more like children who’ve played together forever. There’s very playful and extremely catchy about their music that makes our bodies quiver each time we hear them.\r\n\r\nSuburban Kids with Biblical Names are Johan Hedberg and Peter Gunnarsson. They make and record their music in the hallway or the storehouse at the home of Peter’s kind parents. Johan makes simple drafts of the songs and then Peter polish them and turn them into shiny pop songs.\r\n\r\nThey put two songs on an internet site in the beginning of 2004 and got very good response from people. The Sonic magazine got in touch and interviewed them and put a song on their compilation. Soon after this they were signed to Labrador Records.\r\n\r\nIn 2005 Labrador released their debut album simply called #3 which not only reached the charts in Sweden and got amazing reviews here - it was somewhat of a slowly growing world wide success. The album was released late 2006 North America and in 2007 the UK.\r\n\r\nThe kids are right now working on a new EP, presumably to be named #4, due to be released in November/December 2008 and a new album which should be out in the spring of 2009\r\n\r\nwww.skwbn2008.blogspot.com'),
(6480, 'The Legends', 'http://www.indievox.com/thelegends', 'http://cdn-data.indievox.com/indievox_user/30000/6480/pix/6480180X180.jpg?1427770888', 7, 'The Legends 傳奇樂團，由Club 8主腦Johan Angergard領軍，集結Acid House Kings、Starlet、Aerospace、Airliner樂團成員而成的Labrador廠牌超級樂團，印證了現今瑞典清新音樂更摩登成熟的氣候，並且傳承了那永遠可愛粗糙的精神。整張專輯所呈現的是吉他噪音、手鈴鼓、拍手聲和無邪合音，是Television Personalities的天真低能，是Comet Gain的車庫流行，更是屬於瑞典的清新靈魂跳動。保持了原有特色的Club 8或Acid House Kings式輕吟合唱外，加上了明亮旋律和低調電子節拍為主的淡淡憂傷樂風，揉合著New Order、Felt、Feelies等經典名字以及早期The Cure式後龐克影響而來。\r\nThe Legends was formed in January 2003 and the week after a gig was booked, supporting The Radio Dept. in Stockholm. As the band basically lacked songs and members the first two weeks were spent writing songs and gathering friends who could play, or wanted to play, in the band.\r\n\r\nAccording to The Legends the band play music that can''t be placed in a genre, still they''re happy to agree on Television Personalities, Comet Gain, Motown and C-86 as inspiration.\r\n\r\n"When they write their best uptempo songs, time stands still. Handclap, sing-a-long choruses and clattering guitars, soul" says The Cricket. We agree!\r\n\r\nThe Legends are nine persons who play drums, guitars, tambourine, organ, bass and sings. Many of the members have never played their instruments before which just adds excitement to the short and intensive gigs.'),
(6482, 'South Ambulance', 'http://www.indievox.com/southambulance', 'http://cdn2-data.indievox.com/indievox_user/30000/6482/pix/6482180X180.jpg?1427770888', 2, 'South Ambulance 南方救護樂團，Labrador旗下最讓Dream/Noise-Pop樂迷引頸期盼的新名字。透過那股憤怒的青春吶喊，展現出源自Ride、My Bloody Valentine、Jesus & Mary Chain、Television Personalities等的音樂影響。\r\n原先四人組(Pietu Kaipainen、Robin Spurrier、Daniel Filipsson、Daniel Gamba)的陣容在鍵琴手Stefan Lindstrom加入後，首張同名專輯也與之發表。不僅僅只有單純野性的吉他噪音無限充斥，South Ambulance彷彿重現80年代時的Creation Records，每一場狂亂聞名的The Living Room夜晚。\r\nThe Stockholm band South Ambulance was formed in late 2003 by Pietu Kaipainen, Daniel Filipsson, Robin Spurrier & Daniel Gamba, with the ambition to write good music on Saturdays and record it on Sundays. In November the same year, four songs were caught on tape and the band was offered to do their first live set at a club in Stockholm. The audience was happy, Swedish radio started to play the music and magazines wrote nice words so the band decided to put out their ep#1 on cd-r. “Die 5times times5”, their first recording, was spread on the internet and became kind of a hit in Sweden. During 2004 south ambulance did gigs, recorded more songs, participated on compilations and released ep#2 & ep#3, still with great support from fans, radio and magazines.\r\n\r\nIn January 2005 friend & percussion/keyboard player Stefan Lindström joined the band. Sonic magazine put “Saturdays for sad excuses” on their compilation sonically speaking. More concerts, radio airplay and song writing led the band to finally sell its soul and sign with Labrador. Their first album was released on the 23rd of march 2005. When this biography was written south ambulance just finished their recording of the pale saints song “kinky love” which will be on an English indie cover compilation published by London based AC30. South ambulance may not be a Sunday band anymore.'),
(6494, '午後之樹', 'http://www.indievox.com/afternoontree', 'http://cdn-data.indievox.com/indievox_user/user180X180.png?1427770889', 1, 'Afternoon Tree 是一個理想性很高的夢幻組合！成立於2006年，三位背景迥異的團員，卻混搭成了從未想見的音樂潮流。團長Toshi擔任口琴手、配上Mountain的木吉他、以及Annie的大提琴，看似簡樸卻不單調，更沒想到合奏起來卻是那麼的悅耳、動人。'),
(6503, 'Code Anchor', 'http://www.indievox.com/codeanchor', 'http://cdn1-data.indievox.com/indievox_user/30000/6503/pix/6503180X180.jpg?1427770889', 6, 'Meet Code Anchor:\r\n\r\nCode Anchor was born and bred in Commack, New York. Originally founded by the core songwriting duo of Dan Keller and Ryan Schiff, the line-up has since evolved into the current 4-piece roster, including bassist Bill Burns and drummer Scotty Zwang.\r\n\r\nTheir goal from the start was to write and perform songs that are melodic, catchy, explosive, intelligent, dance-able and most of all... original. Code Anchor has an innumerable amount of influences, which encompass such genres as rock, jazz, punk, hip-hop, reggae, metal, funk, bossa nova, bluegrass, and, of course, video game music.\r\n\r\nGigging since 2003, Code Anchor has performed all over the east coast and are currently looking to book a Winter''08/Spring''09 tour cross country. They have released two EPs and just recently a full length album, soon to be available for order online and on iTunes.\r\n\r\nAccolades:\r\n\r\nErnie Ball Warped Tour Battle of the Bands winners 2008\r\n\r\nLong Island Goodtimes Music Festival winners 2006\r\n\r\nGNYC M.E.A.N.Y.fest winners 2006\r\n\r\nDiscography:\r\n\r\nRosada (2008)\r\n\r\nTall Tales From The Moon (2007)\r\n\r\nSolamente Code Anchor (2005) '),
(6522, '五彩呼倫貝爾兒童合唱團', 'http://www.indievox.com/5wccs', 'http://cdn-data.indievox.com/indievox_user/30000/6522/pix/6522180X180.jpg?1427770889', 2, '這是一支由呼倫貝爾草原上的鄂倫春、鄂溫克、達斡爾三個少數民族及布里亞特、巴爾虎兩個草原部落的37名孩子組成的中國第一個較少數民族兒童合唱團，年齡從最小的5歲到最大的13歲。他們之中有三分之二生活在北中國最邊遠的牧區、森林和農莊。\r\n\r\n草原的孩子八歲已能馴服野馬，曾親眼看見親人死在風雪中，父母親遠去放牧，只能與老祖母相依為命。他們是馴服過野馬的小騎手，他們是根本不識譜的鄉下孩子，他們是來自草原深處普通牧人的後代。他們有著不同於一般人的童年，沒有遊戲機，沒有麥當勞，沒有呵護和嬌寵，只有兒時父母和奶奶教的歌謠，伴隨他們成長。\r\n\r\n孩子們的歌聲裡有大自然，有山巒，有河流，還有小溪；有生活，有愛情，有勞動，還有遊戲；有馬背民族的雄風，有狩獵民族的悠然，有女人的溫婉，男人的豪氣，也有孩童的俏皮。來自草原深處的孩子們以天使般的歌喉、用五種母語演繹一首首動人的草原歌謠。而這些稚嫩聲音後隱含著蒼涼與厚重，能猝不及防地把我們帶到一片廣袤草原與五個民族的歷史相遇，從而發現一片純淨美麗的新世界……\r\n');
