(9934, 'Paul Oakenfold', 'http://www.indievox.com/pauloakenfold', 'http://cdn1-data.indievox.com/indievox_user/30000/9934/pix/9934180X180.jpg?1427770966', 1, 'Paul Oakenfold (born August 30, 1963 in Greenhithe, Kent[1] England) is a world famous DJ and producer, whose works have helped define the mainstream of trance.\r\n\r\nNot only does Paul Oakenfold produce records, but he also mixes them. In 1987 he spent several months in Ibiza with a few friends and fell in love with dance club music. Oakenfold produced “Happy Mondays’ Pills ‘n’ Thrills and Bellyaches” before producing for U2, Massive Attack, Simply Red and New Order (to name a few), many of which were released on his label Perfecto Records.\r\n\r\nIn 1999 after building an American fanbase he released “Tranceport” which was widely accepted by American trance fans.\r\n\r\nAfter “Tranceport” came “Perfecto Presents Another World” which was arguably his most successful album, as it introduced millions more to his style. \r\n\r\nHis popularity grew as many of his works were inclulded in movie soundtracks such as Swordfish, The Matrix Reloaded, The Matrix Revolutions, Die Another Day (where he remixed the James Bond theme before later going to work on the videogame Goldeneye: Rogue Agent in 2004) and Collateral.\r\n\r\nIn 2002 he released Bunkka, which featured the hit single ‘Starry-Eyed Surprise’. In the same year, Oakenfold was listed in Q’s “50 Bands to see Before you Die” compilition.\r\n\r\n2004 brought about the double album ‘Creamfields’, but it was in 2005 that he released the Perfecto Album entitled ‘Perfecto Presents The Club’.\r\n\r\nHe also released the album Great Wall, recorded live at the Great Wall of China.'),
(9937, '硬式紅茶', 'http://www.indievox.com/harjustmusic', 'http://cdn2-data.indievox.com/indievox_user/30000/9937/pix/9937180X180.jpg?1427770966', 174, '直接、簡單、明瞭 就是“硬式紅茶”充滿活力與熱情的活力與曲風。\n\n硬式紅茶 樂團，是由一群熱愛音樂的熱血青年所組成的樂團，\n從2007年底開始，到現在2012年經過了四個多年頭的日子以來，\n他們經歷過了團員之間的理念不合及夢想與現實殘酷的打擊。\n而越多的打擊，卻也讓他們對音樂的熱愛更深、更不願妥協的態度。\n\n在2012/05/31 發行首張EP, EP名為“抬抬頭”,也就是主打歌曲。 \n抬抬頭 一個自然的動作，但又能讓人放鬆、振奮的意思。\nEP所要傳達的意境是，每個人都會有現況，做為背景所寫的一首故事,\n 歌曲裡將會傳遞 民謠, 流行, 動感的氣氛, 並且交代我們的主要風格，\n大調的熱情、開心與動感，讓你聽到“硬式紅茶“的image與style，\n 馬上就會在你腦海裡浮現出來。\n\n音樂創作上主攻PopMusic，也嘗試在創作中加進任何音樂及好玩的元素。\n作自己想做的音樂，一直是T.B.T.的最高原則，不論新聞時事、\n感情世界或是出社會的衰小事，都是創作的靈感。\n我們一貫的創作理念是：將煩惱放進歌裡，用音樂的力量發洩出來！\n再負面的情緒都要用正面的力量發想！衝擊到每個人心中搖滾的小宇宙！\n燃燒吧，甩掉煩躁、用力聽音樂，跟我們一起揮霍僅剩不多的青春吧！\n\n在2013 跟幾個同好組成了yamama fsuion band~之後 也就一起跟硬式紅茶加入了演出。\n當流行搖滾音樂歌曲與jazz音樂的融合樂 碰撞在一起時，會產生出更好聽更好玩的火花。\n\n\n'),
(9938, 'Ian Livingstone', 'http://www.indievox.com/ianlivingstone', 'http://cdn3-data.indievox.com/indievox_user/30000/9938/pix/9938180X180.jpg?1427770966', 0, ''),
(9939, 'Chris Tilton', 'http://www.indievox.com/christilton', 'http://cdn1-data.indievox.com/indievox_user/30000/9939/pix/9939180X180.jpg?1427770966', 0, 'Chris Tilton, a New Orleans, Louisiana, native, was born June 9, 1979. He obtained his Bachelor of Music Composition degree from the University of the Arts (Philadelphia) in 2001 under the instruction of Prof. Andrew Rudin. For many years, Chris knew that he wanted to concentrate his efforts in the music and film industry so, after graduating, he made the move to Los Angeles.\r\n\r\nIn L.A., composer Michael Giacchino took Chris under his wing and he began working as his assistant on the television show Alias. Soon after, Chris began doing additional orchestration on several of Michael’s projects, including The Incredibles, The Family Stone and most recently, Mission: Impossible III.\r\n\r\nIn 2004, Michael wrote the main theme for the video game, Mercenaries, and encouraged Chris to write what was to be his first large orchestral score. Since then, the two collaborated on the main theme for the video game, Black, with Chris writing yet another sizable orchestral score. Beginning in the 4th season of Alias, Chris wrote additional music until the series ended in May of 2006.\r\n\r\nWith this invaluable experience, Chris is undertaking individual projects and is currently writing the score to the video game, Mercenaries 2, which is set for release in 2007'),
(9940, 'Frank Klepacki', 'http://www.indievox.com/frankklepacki', 'http://cdn-data.indievox.com/indievox_user/30000/9940/pix/9940180X180.jpg?1427770966', 0, 'Frank Klepacki is one of the foremost modern composers for Video Games Music. He is currently the lead composer for Petroglyph Games, formed when Westwood Studios closed due to a take over by Electronic Arts.\r\n\r\nHe is most commonly known for his soundtracks to the Command &amp; Conquer franchise, a few notable tracks include Hell March, Act on Instinct and Just Do It Up. Frank’s fusion of electronic, metal, and hints of industrial influence were key to making Command &amp; Conquer the best selling real time strategy series, with an excess of 35 million units sold (Wikipedia). He has also composed music for Westwood Studio’s Dune games, Lands of Lore, and Blade Runner. Frank’s most recent work is featured on EA Los Angeles’s newest addition to the C&amp;C franchise; “Command &amp; Conquer Red Alert 3”. Frank composed both a new version of Hell March and Grinder (Hell March 3 and Grinder 2 respectively) on this soundtrack, as well as a new Soviet combat theme, but otherwise, this was his sole contribution as the rest of the score was completed by other composers.\r\n\r\nIn the late 90’s Frank worked with bands such as I Am and Home Cookin’ as a Drummer, and in 2002 released his first solo album. He has since released another three albums, mostly following the style of music he used for the Command and Conquer series, but also drawing on the style he used with Home Cookin’'),
(9941, 'Steve Jablonsky & Trevor Morris', 'http://www.indievox.com/stevejablonskytrevormorris', 'http://cdn3-data.indievox.com/indievox_user/30000/9941/pix/9941180X180.jpg?1427770966', 0, ''),
(9942, '信息樂團', 'http://www.indievox.com/rockthemessage', 'http://cdn2-data.indievox.com/indievox_user/30000/9942/pix/9942180X180.jpg?1427770966', 8, '成軍七年，以英式搖滾為骨幹，一直活躍於香港獨立樂隊界。曾參與演出包括：Streetvoice HK香港大團誕生開發場、香港龍舟嘉年華．生力暢飲樂園(表演嘉賓)、PolyU HKCC Band Society Annual Performance、浸會大學傳理學會歌唱比賽(表演嘉賓)、中文大學東華三院社區書院歌唱比賽(表演嘉賓)、突破山寨音樂會第一擊、The Message x Fullcupmusic呼吸音樂會、南丫島海上音樂會、我承諾live band show音樂嘉年華及抱擁．菜園村音樂會…等等。\n\n2012年，首支派台歌”還我天空”成功打入香港音樂流行榜第五位。其後發表首個全手繪STOP MOTION MV - "血肉"，引來熱烈迴響及關注。\n\n2013年，同名專輯《THE MESSAGE》正式上市！\n\n曾發行單曲：\n魂歸天國 (2011-09-23)\n還我天空 (2012-03-01)\n血肉 (2012-07-30)\n星月夜 (2013-09-01)\n\n曾發行專輯：\nTHE MESSAGE (2013-09-01)\n\n五位成員包括：主音及貝斯結他手 – Lap Wong、結他手 – Yin Tsang & Cyrus Chiu、鍵琴手 – Steven Pang與及鼓手 – Derrick Lee。各人受不同類型音樂薰陶，游走於流行與另類之間，拼湊出The Message獨有的聲音。而且特別著重歌詞的表達，希望藉音樂唱出生活所見所聞，與聽眾產生共鳴。\n\n網址:\nwww.myspace.com/rockthemessage\nwww.faceboook.com/rockthemessage\nhttp://www.streetvoice.com/rockthemessage\nhttp://www.youtube.com/wailapwong\n'),
(9943, 'Bill Brown & Mikael Sandgren', 'http://www.indievox.com/billbrownmikaelsandgren', 'http://cdn1-data.indievox.com/indievox_user/user180X180.png?1427770966', 0, ''),
(9944, 'melody.', 'http://www.indievox.com/melody', 'http://cdn3-data.indievox.com/indievox_user/30000/9944/pix/9944180X180.jpg?1427770966', 0, 'melody. is a Japanese pop singer who was born on February 24th, 1982 in Honolulu, Hawaii. She started out modeling at the age of 16, but wanted to launch a music career in Japan and did so with the release of her first single, Dreamin’ Away, on February 19th, 2003. It wasn’t until her first collaboration with m-flo on their “m-flo loves…” project that she became more well-known.\r\n\r\nOn October 22, 2008, melody. announced that she will retire from the music industry in January 2009. She plans to enter the fashion industry as a designer of Western-styled clothes.\r\n\r\nFrom April 2007 until October 2008, melody. was the host of J-MELO, an all-English weekly show focused on Japanese music that airs on NHK World TV. Outside of Japan, she may be known for playing the character “Yumi Yamamoto” in Electronic Art’s Need for Speed: Carbon, which also featured the Junkie XL remix of her song FEEL THE RUSH on its soundtrack.'),
(9945, 'Jeremy Soule', 'http://www.indievox.com/jeremysoule', 'http://cdn2-data.indievox.com/indievox_user/30000/9945/pix/9945180X180.jpg?1427770966', 0, 'Jeremy Soule is an award-winning American composer prominent in game music scores. Soule’s soundtracks are often critically acclaimed as being among the best in the computer and video games industry and as rivaling the quality of many orchestral film soundtracks. A large percentage of Soule’s music is done electronically and emulates real orchestral music so well that it is frequently indistinguishable from the real thing. \r\n\r\nHe has produced music for:\r\n\r\n* The Elder Scrolls III: Morrowind\r\n* The Elder Scrolls IV: Oblivion\r\n* The Harry Potter games\r\n* Company of Heroes\r\n* Dungeon Siege\r\n* Dungeon Siege II\r\n* Total Annihilation\r\n* Secret of Evermore\r\n* Neverwinter Nights\r\n* Guild Wars\r\n* Guild Wars: Factions\r\n* Guild Wars: Nightfall\r\n* Guild Wars: Eye of the North\r\n* Warhammer: Mark of Chaos\r\n* Warhammer40K: Dawn of War\r\n* Star Wars: Knights of the Old Republic\r\n* Prey\r\n* Supreme Commander\r\n* Icewind Dale\r\n* Icewind Dale: Heart of Winter.\r\n\r\nJeremy Soule recently took legal action against the Anime and Video Game Soundtrack site known as KHInsider, which was dedicated to keeping rare soundtracks online. The owner of the site decided to shut the site down in order to avoid being sued by Soule, who was not only trying to have his own music removed, but all the music on the site.'),
(9946, 'James Hannigan', 'http://www.indievox.com/jameshannigan', 'http://cdn3-data.indievox.com/indievox_user/30000/9946/pix/9946180X180.jpg?1427770966', 0, 'James Hannigan is a composer with involvement in a variety of industries, but most prominently within the area of interactive entertainment. Starting his career in-house in the mid-1990s after a short stint in television, he later returned to freelance work, basing himself at the world famous Pinewood Studios complex in West London. Since then, James has accumulated four BAFTA nominations for music and a win with Electronic Arts in 2000. His credits include Primeval (ITV), Harry Potter and the Half-Blood Prince, Command and Conquer: Red Alert 3, Harry Potter and The Order of the Phoenix, Freelancer, Republic, Evil Genius, Brute Force, Catwoman, Reign of Fire, Conquest, Grand Prix 4, entries in the Warhammer series, Mr Bean, Sim Theme Park, Lost In Space (film; sound design), entries in the FIFA and F1 series, Privateer: The Darkening and many others. \r\n\r\nAt this time, Video Games Live are touring with a segment of James’s music - recently debuting at London’s Festival Hall and featuring the Philharmonia orchestra. \r\n\r\nParticipating as a panellist at events such as the Edinburgh International Festival, Musicworks and The BAFTA Interactive Festival, James also writes articles and has been featured on the cover of Develop Magazine, profiled in Post, Audio Media, Resolution and other publications. '),
(9953, 'OK BOMB', 'http://www.indievox.com/okbomb', 'http://cdn-data.indievox.com/indievox_user/30000/9953/pix/9953180X180.jpg?1427770966', 17, 'OK BOMB是個炸彈，不是貼傷口的OK繃！充滿著爆發力的音樂，卻又能夠讓你聽的舒服，曲風很難去界定，有點英搖有點日搖有點美搖，總之，就是好聽就對了！ '),
(9957, 'Trevor Jones', 'http://www.indievox.com/trevorjones', 'http://cdn1-data.indievox.com/indievox_user/30000/9957/pix/9957180X180.jpg?1427770966', 0, 'Trevor Alfred Charles Jones (born March 23, 1949 in Cape Town, South Africa) is an orchestral film score composer. He is known for his work on Excalibur (1981) The Dark Crystal (1982) Angel Heart (1987) The Last of the Mohicans (1992) Cliffhanger (1993) Dark City (1998) Desperate Measures/The Mighty (1998) From Hell (2001) Dinotopia (2002) Loch Ness/Aegis (2005) and many more. Climax of his career: a live album recorded in 2006 at the Soncinemad festival. Versatility, sensitivity, taste for majestic themes and orchestral control, here is all the talent of Trevor Jones.'),
(9970, '尻樂團', 'http://www.indievox.com/kaoboyz', 'http://cdn3-data.indievox.com/indievox_user/30000/9970/pix/9970180X180.jpg?1427770966', 15, '尻的創作，都是在唱一些發生在身邊周圍的人事物，愛情的苦澀、生活的瓶頸、\r\n歡笑的時光，我們透過寫歌，用音樂來抒發，這就是我們最單純的出發點！'),
(9979, '心電樂(Heartones)', 'http://www.indievox.com/heartones', 'http://cdn2-data.indievox.com/indievox_user/30000/9979/pix/9979180X180.jpg?1427770967', 312, '時而哀愁冷淡、時而純真童稚的電子聲響，焦躁扭曲的音牆與清徹透亮的音符層層交疊，不按牌理出牌的編曲調式，捉摸不定的鼓點，悅耳流暢的旋律在你的耳邊跳著舞。\n心電樂訴說著荒誕奇異的、甜蜜浪漫的、憂鬱傷感的故事，而你我都是主角。\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n                                                                 \n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n'),
(9981, '非人物種', 'http://www.indievox.com/inhuman', 'http://cdn-data.indievox.com/indievox_user/30000/9981/pix/9981180X180.jpg?1427770967', 480, '現實拖磨少年時的夢，生活跟理想你要選那一項？\r\n這是成為男子漢的必經路程。\r\n\r\n踏著黑紫色的雲彩，口中哼著不成調的音階來到人世間，三頭六臂手持雞腿降臨凡間，帶給俗世人們無盡的苦惱與納悶，毫無頭緒的前奏，騎虎難下的主歌，風流倜儻的副歌與不知所措的結語，狂亂的嘶吼猶如天蓬元帥下凡，雜亂無章的演奏彷彿春天的水溝，帶給你莫名奇妙又充滿快感帶點尷尬的氛圍。\r\n\r\n才氣充滿的粗獷4人樂隊專門救災，切西瓜。\r\n\r\n非人物種（Inhuman）\r\n\r\nfacebook:http://www.facebook.com/Inhumanband\r\nContact : inhumanbandok@gmail.com\r\n\r\n或撥0980390343阿顯\r\n或撥0980110701撥屎\r\n'),
(9985, '激膚樂團', 'http://www.indievox.com/msays', 'http://cdn2-data.indievox.com/indievox_user/30000/9985/pix/9985180X180.jpg?1427770967', 518, '來自台北的激膚，從2010年成團至今，已有許多國家城市音樂節演出經驗，曾受邀於日本、韓國、加拿大、荷蘭、德國，中港澳...等地演出。\n\n激膚於2012年發行的同名EP，獲得了第三屆金音創作獎【最佳樂團】【最佳搖滾單曲】與【最佳樂手】等獎項，並入圍第二十四屆金曲獎【最佳樂團】與第三屆金音創作獎【最佳現場】。\n\n樂團由主唱安卓雅與貝斯手尤世儒所組成，安卓雅曾在加拿大演出時，被當地媒體形容為 - 天生的搖滾巨星，尤世儒獨特的演奏方式在2013年獲得了金音獎最佳樂手。\n\n目前激膚正在籌備樂團首張專輯，並預計於2014年發行。\n'),
(9987, 'Michael Giacchino', 'http://www.indievox.com/michaelgiacchino', 'http://cdn2-data.indievox.com/indievox_user/30000/9987/pix/9987180X180.jpg?1427770967', 0, 'Michael Giacchino (pronounced juh-kee-no) (born 1967, Riverside, New Jersey) is an American soundtrack composer who has composed several multi-award winning scores for many popular movies, television series and video games. His scores are notable for their usage of brass. He attended the Evening Division at the Juilliard School, as well as the School of Visual Arts in New York City, where he acquired a degree in film production and a minor degree in History.\r\n\r\nCompositions in Video Games\r\n\r\nGiacchino’s first major composition was for the DreamWorks video game adaptation of the 1997 movie, The Lost World: Jurassic Park. The video game was the first PlayStation (also on Sega Saturn) console title to be recorded with an original live orchestral score. Giacchino has since continued his relationship with DreamWorks, providing full orchestral scores for many of their popular videogames. Giacchino’s award-winning compositions covers the first four Medal of Honor series, (Underground, Allied Assault and Frontline, along with the original Medal of Honor). He has also provided scores for several other World War II-related video games like Secret Weapons Over Normandy, Call of Duty and Call of Duty: Finest Hour. Additionally, Giacchino wrote the main theme for Mercenaries while composer Chris Tilton provided the rest of the underscore. Giacchino also composed themes for The Incredibles: Rise of the Underminer, and co-wrote the theme from Black with composer Chris Tilton. He also composed the score for Alias, which was based on the television series of the same name.'),
(9996, 'Christopher Lennertz', 'http://www.indievox.com/christopherlennertz', 'http://cdn-data.indievox.com/indievox_user/30000/9996/pix/9996180X180.jpg?1427770967', 0, 'Christopher Lennertz (born January 2, 1972) is a composer, arranger, producer and conducter of video games, films, television shows, and records. He was born in Boston, and moved to Easton, Pennsylvania at age 9, where he then began professional music training, learning to play the trumpet and the guitar. He studied composition, jazz arranging and theory in high school. He attended The University of Southern California’s Thorton School of Music where he met Eric Kripke, the creator of the TV show supernatural. He collaborated with Kripke on two short films, one of which won the Audience Award at the Slamdance film festival. He would later work with Kripke again on the score for Supernatural. He worked for composers Basil Poledouris and Michael Kamen after college.\r\n\r\nIn 2002, Cinemusic named him Best New Composer for his work on Clive Barker’s ‘Saint Sinner’, and this score was named one of the top ten scores of the year by the Film Music Review. He collaborated with Ozomatli on their record ‘Street Signs’, which won a Grammy award for Best Latin Rock Album. In 2004, EA awarded him an Interactive Academy Award for his work on ‘Medal of Honor: Rising Sun’, the first of three ‘Medal of Honor’ games composed by him. He scored the music from ‘Supernatural’ in conjunction with composer Jay Gruska, and was nominated for an Emmy Award in 2006 for his score for the pilot episode.'),
(9997, 'Ekstrak', 'http://www.indievox.com/ekstrak', 'http://cdn1-data.indievox.com/indievox_user/user180X180.png?1427770967', 1, ''),
(10000, 'Paul Linford', 'http://www.indievox.com/paullinford', 'http://cdn1-data.indievox.com/indievox_user/30000/10000/pix/10000180X180.jpg?1427770967', 0, 'Paul Linford is a music composer best known for his work on the score for the EA game Need For Speed: Most Wanted. He also frequently works with film score composer Trevor Rabin and has composed additional music for almost all of his projects. He is also credited as producer/score mixer on many of them.'),
(10003, 'Jim Latham', 'http://www.indievox.com/jimlatham', 'http://cdn1-data.indievox.com/indievox_user/30000/10003/pix/10003180X180.jpg?1427770967', 0, ''),
