(14471, '液態衝擊樂團', 'http://www.indievox.com/liquidpunch', 'http://cdn2-data.indievox.com/indievox_user/30000/14471/pix/14471180X180.jpg?1427771065', 87, '我們是來自台北的樂團，於2008年組成至今，主要曲風走向為Alternative Rock、Indie Rock。歌曲主要以主唱李方有些頹廢、迷幻的唱腔，加上各團員對於不同風格喜好所融和出屬於我們自己獨特的音樂類型。在2010年夏天兩位團員陸續退伍後，再次積極地尋找各種演出機會，讓大家聽見我們的音樂。\r\n\r\n歷經了四年的洗煉，從學生到入社會，從國軍Online到退伍，可想而知液態衝擊樂團歷經了許多麻煩事，但我們始終堅持我們所想要的，我們帶來的是最新的中文單曲，以及更加成熟的表演方式。\r\n　　為了讓自己與觀眾更加的投入「當下」對音樂的熱愛，與其他樂團一樣我們都花了時間練習，也不斷的在彼此溝通與互相激勵當中成長。這些努力其實都只是我們必定經過的路，最主要的是我們希望讓更多的觀眾們發現地下樂團有著多樣化的曲風，以及別具特色的表演形式。\r\n　　在現場表演的當下，無論你是否能理解我們，能否接受這樣的聲音，我們都將完整的表現出我們的熱愛、我們的厭惡、我們的歇斯底里！\r\n'),
(14504, '陳建年', 'http://www.indievox.com/paudull', 'http://cdn-data.indievox.com/indievox_user/30000/14504/pix/14504180X180.jpg?1427771066', 101, 'Pau-dull, whose Chinese name is Chen Jian-Nian, is a policeman from Taiwan''s southeastern Tai-Dong County. An Aboriginal singer-songwriter of the Puyuma tribe, his first album, “Ho-Hai-Yan Ocean,” was released in 1999 and the next year was awarded a Golden Melody Award (the Taiwan equivalent of a Grammy) for best vocalist and best songwriter. Pau-dull plays folk music that expresses the beauty of the mountains and ocean of his ancestral home. His songs combine American folk music, blues, jazz, but are also deeply rooted in the tradition of his Aboriginal heritage. Pau-dull achieved massive popular success in the wake of his Golden Melody Awards, but has maintained a simple and low-profile lifestyle, resisting the temptation to leave the remote southeast coast for the material enticements of Taipei. Despite being one of the most popular and respected musicians in Taiwan, Pau-dull still works as a police officer in his hometown of Tai-Dong. In 2000 Pau-dull released “How Deep is the Ocean,” a solo guitar album from the soundtrack of a documentary of the same name. In 2001 he released a live album of a performance with Aboriginal singer-songwriter Panai, “Pau-dull and Panai Live”. In 2002 he released his second album “Mother Earth.”\r\n歌詠海洋，盛讚大地，暢飲太平洋的風\r\n如果陳明章是台灣最後的民謠傳奇、素人歌手，那麼陳建年將是來自花東海岸的部落傳奇、警察歌手。十八歲他開始音樂創作，他的歌早已在各部落傳唱已久。他的吉他融合藍調與新世紀曲風，功力神奇高強之處，常被吉他愛好者奉為圭臬。早年曾幫張惠妹伴奏吉他，是阿妹在台東時的偶像。\r\n聽他的音樂，彷彿閉上眼，就儼然見到東部遼闊的海岸，濤滔海聲以及卑南山下青翠蔓延的部落風情。他清亮的嗓音及如吟遊詩人般的吉他聲，常令人宛如進入一處音樂神祕的海灘。其音樂靈活而大量地運用採擷的環境聲及隨性所致的即興演唱與對白，不僅魅惑著都市人對田野生活的渴望，也成為在外打拼的原住民們心靈上的寄託。想像自己快樂徜徉，臉上始終掛著微笑，空氣裡還有一抹清新氣息。那是一股沁人心肺的人生樂音，發自丹田，穿過侯間，悠悠盪盪自在揮灑開來。'),
(14506, '恆春兮', 'http://www.indievox.com/rzx135cctw', 'http://cdn2-data.indievox.com/indievox_user/30000/14506/pix/14506180X180.jpg?1427771066', 17, 'Hing-Chun is a motorcycle repairman in Kao-hsuing, Taiwan. Despite completing only a Jr. High School education, in the mid-90''s he created and underground radio show that delved deep into social, political, environmental, and minority issues of Taiwan. In a culture dominated by mainstream academic qualifications and Mandarin Chinese, Hung-Chun''s radio talk show is a preservation and transmission of the rich and beautiful oral tradition of the Taiwanese language. All TCM''s previous releases have been music albums; this album of spoken words is a special exception, chosen to present the perspective of the working class on Taiwanese society. It is a rich, fascinating, and unique expression of a point of view too often lost in the cacophonous clamor of mainstream media. \r\n\r\n風行寶島 暢銷全球\r\n「恆春兮」是一個在港都高雄修摩托車的黑手。雖然只有高中學歷，卻能夠自編自導一套讓知識分子驚奇的脫口秀！自成一格的生猛台語，百變廣播劇、奇人怪事新聞、什麼都賣的工商服務，以虛構、倒錯、模仿的方式，隱喻真實生活，達到反諷、戲謔、揶揄的效果。他的創作，繼承了台灣民間口語文學的優良傳統，充分運用台語的音意韻腳，以天馬行空的想像和細膩的生活觀察，表達他對台灣政治、社會、環保、生活、教育…的關懷，更達到寓教於樂的目的！想去老返童，增強體力的男女老少，絕對不能錯過的良藥秘方！\r\n\r\n看到恆春兮本人，絕對會驚訝他竟是如此年青，不太敢置信這位聲音充滿中年男子渾厚感，台語流利且道地的台語廣播秀主持人，今年才三十歲出頭。戴著一副黑框塑膠古味大眼鏡，恆春兮是一位在港都高雄開機車行的老闆。年紀輕，可是退伍後開機車行至今也已經七年了。大部分的時間，恆春兮一如大部分勤奮刻苦的黑手，從早到晚一天超過十二個小時開店為民服務修機車，遇到飆車意外多時，還得星期天加班。\r\n恆春兮和廣播的第一次接觸，是早自1995年參與蕃薯之聲地下廣播電台主持「蕃薯有夠俗」節目。當時地下電台大部分的節目都在談論政治，來主持的人，多是有名的學者專家，恆春兮想做些不一樣的內容，反正是深夜時段，不會砸了電台推動政治改革的招牌。在懷舊的節目主幹中，恆春兮費心的安排幾個小單元：新聞插播、廣播劇、工商服務，戲謔而深刻的內容，再加上恆春兮豐富的聲音表情和靈活的語言運用，使聽眾在收聽時事評論之餘，得以換個心情娛樂一番。「恆春兮工商服務」專輯，就是收錄這些精彩的小單元。\r\n因為恆春兮堅持創作的絕對自主，所以當電台逐漸悖離創台理想時，恆春兮寧願離開也不願妥協，恆春兮說，「再做下去就不好玩了！人生還有許多好玩的事！爬山、釣魚、玩車，唱歌，不一定非要做電台！有笑話可以講給朋友聽，講給來修車的客人聽，還是有聽眾啊！」\r\n為什麼叫恆春兮，這是因為他常常在節目中彈月琴，而月琴是屏東恆春的代表性樂器，聽友便開始叫他《恆春兮》，幾年下來，朋友都叫他的外號，反而沒有人叫他本名！'),
(14507, '波賓樂團', 'http://www.indievox.com/bobinandthemantra', 'http://cdn3-data.indievox.com/indievox_user/30000/14507/pix/14507180X180.jpg?1427771066', 2, 'BOBIN BAJRACHARYA\r\nBorn in Patan of Kathmandu Valley, a capitol city of Himalayan country\r\nNEPAL. Being very much influenced by hard rock music at early age, he\r\nultimately fell in for Bob Marley and Bob Dylan. He got inspiration from\r\nmany western musicians as well as a few Nepali musicians.  He took up guitar\r\nat the age of sixteen for the love of Rock and Roll. He also started to\r\nwrite his own words and music at the same time.  He never had any formal\r\neducation or any kind of guidance in music.  His music and his words are his\r\ntrue feelings, which comes out naturally.  His greatest teacher in his\r\nmusical career is inspirations, which he believes is more important than\r\neducation for any kind of creativity.  He performed in numerous concerts as\r\na solo artist when he was in Nepal including International Music Festival at\r\nKathmadu in 1996.\r\nHe released his first Album "HEROES OF DREAM" in Nepal in 1996. After that,\r\nhe went to Japan for his further University studies.  Even after going to\r\nJapan, he never deserted music. He released his second album "SAMSARA bobin"\r\nfrom MONSOON RECORD and formed the band "bobin and the mantra" in year\r\n2000.  He released the new album "bobin and the mantra" in 2002 from\r\nMONSOON RECORD with a new line up.\r\nHis words reflect his roots of Buddhist philosophy and Nepal, at the same\r\ntime being very philosophical and poetic.  His basic idea and message\r\nthrough music is living in a Harmony, which is only possible when there is\r\nLove and Respect for each other.\r\n\r\nSAWAN JOSHI\r\nBorn in Kathmandu with a family of musical background as his Grand Father\r\nBhuwan Narayan Joshi was a famous classical singer. Therefore, his father\r\nalso wanted him to learn classical music to continue their family’s legacy\r\nof music. He used to play traditional drums and also instrument called\r\n"Harmonium" in temples with old peoples while he was still very young.\r\nIn his teenage, he was very much interested in eastern as well as western\r\nmusic.  He started taking lessons in Indian Classical Vocal at age of\r\nfourteen and later on, Sitar as well.  He is a graduate of a six-year\r\ndiploma course from Allahbad Music University of India.\r\nHe has performed in numerous concerts in Nepal such as International Music\r\nDay and has been a regular performer for National Classical Music Festival\r\nand Radio Nepal''s live shows. Has also won a first place in a classical\r\nmusic competition with his previous group "KALAS" in Nepal.  He is very much\r\ninspired by the artists in eastern classical music, such as Pt.Bhimshen\r\nJoshi (Vocalist), Pt.Ravi Shankar (Sitar) etc.\r\nEven though he has a strong background of South Asian Classical Music, his\r\nambition of playing free and innovative music reflects his unique sound.  In\r\nApril 2000, he went to Japan for his further study, where he met with\r\n"bobin and the mantra" and eventually became a band member.\r\n\r\n玉木智子\r\nBorn in 東京 and raised in 千葉県, she started her music career\r\nwith a Saxophone as she joined a Brass Band while still in her Junior High\r\nSchool.  She was in to CLASSICAL and JAZZ music and later on, in to Latin\r\nmusic like SALSA、MERENGUE、BRAZILIAN too.  In 1988, she went to BERKLEE\r\nCOLLAGE OF MUSIC for her further study in music and graduated.  She was very\r\nmuch involved in Latin Music Scene in America. She also expanded her\r\ninstruments like Flute and Percussions.\r\nIn 1995, she came back to Japan performed as a Saxophone player in various\r\nmusic scenes, such as Jazz Big Band, Musicals and on Televisions.  She also\r\nplayed in a Jazz Funk Band, DNA and in 1998; she got married to 哲太郎,\r\nher co-band member.\r\nIn 1999, 智子 and 哲太郎 formed a duo called "IRUKAPPAS" and also the\r\nindependent record label, MONSOON RECORD.  This was a starting platform\r\ntoward making and producing the music they really like.\r\nA big change came in her life around this time as sickness changes her\r\nattitude toward life style and music drastically.  She is now totally in to\r\nOrganic Foods, Ecological, Simple and Peaceful life, and music being her\r\ngreatest tool in achieving it.\r\n\r\n玉木哲太郎\r\nBorn in 沖縄, most south Island of 日本.  He started playing at 7 and\r\nformed his first band at 14.  He goes to Tokyo at the age 18 and starts\r\nplaying Bass Guitar.  He is very much influenced by YMO, Black Music like\r\nFunk and Soul, Reggae, Tribal Music etc.  At the end of 1995, his band\r\n "UNLIMITED EDITION", which he has been leading since his collage days,\r\nmakes\r\na major debut with album "PLEASURE" from MERCURY MUSIC ENTERTAINMENT.\r\nAfter that changing the band''s name to DNA, he performed in numerous\r\nconcerts in the Live Houses and streets around Tokyo. They also did 沖縄\r\ntour twice.  He has also worked as music arranger and studio musician.  In\r\n1997 spring, he gives a halt to his music career, as he was not satisfied\r\nwith it.  He takes a time to re-set his attitude toward life-style and the\r\nmusic he wants to do.  In the mean time, in 1998 he get married to 智子,\r\nhis co-band member in DNA.\r\nIn 1999, 智子 and 哲太郎 formed a duo called "IRUKAPPAS" and also the\r\nindependent record label, MONSOON RECORD. This was a starting platform\r\ntoward making and producing the music they really like.  He has produced\r\nnumber of albums by different musicians till now.\r\n\r\nBIRTH OF "bobin and the mantra"\r\nLife is not just a co-incidence but it is a destiny.  We are supposed to\r\nmeet not only by a chance because every effect has a cause.\r\nIt was a fine spring day of the year 1999; 智子 and 哲太郎 had just\r\nstarted their interest in Farming and were helping out a Farmer friend 吉田\r\n篤\r\nin his Rice Field.  On that same day, Udaya who was a student from Nepal at\r\n千葉大学 doing his major in Soil Physics was also there to give\r\nhelping hand to 篤.  On their way back home they were more than surprised\r\nto come to know that their houses were only couple of blocks from each\r\nother.  And yet they would have never met before after living there for\r\nalmost three years.\r\nUdaya asked 智子 and 哲太郎 to come over his place for a cup of Tea.\r\nAs they were in Uadaya''s house talking and drinking tea, he comes to know\r\nthat they are both musicians.  Udaya also tells them that his roommate from\r\nNepal and currently a university student was a musician too and asks them if\r\nthey would like to listen to his music.  Udaya played the tape of his music\r\nfor them and there was something in that voice they heard on that tape,\r\nwhich clicked in their hearts.  That voice and music was of Bobin who was\r\nintroduced by Udaya to 智子 and 哲太郎 a week later.  Previously, a friend\r\n池田 introduced\r\nBobin to 篤 then Bobin introduced Udaya to 篤, as he wanted to do some\r\npractical fieldwork for his studies.  This was indeed a destiny.\r\nFew weeks later, there was party on occasion of newly established NPO by a\r\nfriend.  They decided to perform few songs as a session with line up of\r\nBobin (vocal, guitar), Udaya(tabla, madal), 智子 (flute, saxophone) and\r\n哲太郎 (bass).  It was session band just for fun of it.  This first\r\nperformance went very well with the audience and relation between these four\r\ntoo.\r\nThis started to move in the direction of recording and releasing the songs\r\nwritten by Bobin since he came to Japan and which he had recorded as a demo\r\ntape.  This idea began to take shape and the album "SAMSARA bobin" was\r\nreleased through MONSOON RECORD in year 2000, which was owned by 哲太郎.\r\nAfter recording the album they needed a band to perform the songs as it is\r\nin the CD.  Naturally, Udaya, 智子 and 哲太郎 all together started off\r\nas a band as they had also participated in Bobin''s album.  Now they were\r\ncalled "bobin and the mantra".\r\nBut soon after that in March 2000, the band was in verse of collapse as\r\nUdaya was going back to Nepal after his graduation.  In this mean time,\r\nthere came news of coming of new student from Nepal in Bobin''s university\r\nand who was a musician too.  He came to Japan on April, a few weeks after\r\nUdaya went back to Nepal and this was Sawan Joshi a classically trained\r\nmusician who played Sitar, Tabla and Madal.  After a jam up session, he\r\npromptly joined  "bobin and the mantra" in a nick of time.  After that they\r\nreleased the album "bobin and the mantra" in year 2001 summer.\r\nSince then the band has played in numerous concerts mostly around 東京\r\narea.  They have also toured around 日本 and there twice 北海道 Tours\r\nwere the most amazing ones.  These tours proved to be yet another destiny\r\nfor the band as they met with 塚田高哉 from "TAU"  band.  "TAU"  band is a\r\nunique folk song band from 北海道.  高哉 was one of the concert\r\norganizers for "bobin and the mantra" in 東川, 北海道 Tour.  We\r\nalso had nice time jamming up with the Ainu Musician "OKI" in 東川.\r\nMeeting wonderful human like 高哉 was not just a co-incidence it was a\r\ndestiny who introduced "bobin and the mantra" to TCM in Taiwan.\r\n"bobin and the mantra" sent their CD to TCM in Taiwan in summer of 2002.\r\nThe plugs clicked just like that and in July "bobin and the mantra"\r\nperformed at "HO-HAI-YAN Rock Festival" in Taiwan.  And here they\r\nare, "bobin and the mantra" is releasing their album in Taiwan in January\r\n2003.\r\n\r\nMESSAGE FROM THE BAND\r\nFirst, we are very happy to release our music in Taiwan.  Thank You very\r\nmusch and hope you will enjoy our music.\r\n"bobin and the mantra" consists of four individuals having different back\r\ngrounds and roots of music.  In this band we are trying to cross over the\r\nbarriers of roots and back ground to create totally a new kind of music,\r\nwhich is only possible through spiritual unity and respect for each other.\r\nWe use ethnic and tribal as well as western standard musical instruments.\r\nBut our goals are not just to create ethnic music.  Our goal is to create\r\nwhole new dimension of musical world.  Not commercialized music but Root\r\nmusic, which is really inside our heart.  We want to create music without\r\nany logic or calculation and we want to play music from depth our heart,\r\nwhich is the real message and power of Music.\r\nMusic again is a non-destructive weapon for us.  For us it is a tool to\r\nspread a message of Love, Peace and Respect around the world.  We believe\r\nthat there will be no Love and Peace in this world until the day we start\r\nrespecting each other.  We must respect each other’s Religion, Culture,\r\nRace, Earth, Land, Air, Sea, Life, Sky, Universe………………… like we\r\nrespect our MOTHER.  Only then we could see real Peace and Love in our world\r\nand we can live in harmony.\r\nOur music is a harmony between different roots.  This is our special message\r\nfor everybody out there, Harmony.  So lets us work together for Love, Peace\r\nand Respect.\r\nLastly, we would like to thank our Parents, Friends, All TCM staffs, God,\r\nInspiration and you for reading this.\r\nBE HAPPY\r\n\r\n'),
(14509, 'JOKER', 'http://www.indievox.com/jokerband', 'http://cdn2-data.indievox.com/indievox_user/30000/14509/pix/14509180X180.jpg?1427771066', 362, '2004年結成。在2006年陸續參加各大樂團比賽並榮獲佳績，開始活躍於大型音樂祭活動，2009年受邀至廈門、上海、北京演出，並多次與來自日本的樂團一同在台灣舉行巡迴，目前累計演出約三百場。\n\n順口的流行搖滾旋律、單吉他&貝斯&爵士鼓的4人編制樂團。早期翻唱日文歌曲並填寫中文歌詞，逐漸形成偏向日系流行樂團的音樂風格。從傳達音樂的快樂、樂觀態度到分享生活中喜怒哀樂，表現原創音樂最真實的自我。\n\n2011年吉他手和貝斯手相繼入伍，樂團活動休止一年...\n2012年團員退伍後，繼續朝著音樂的夢想大步邁進...\n2013年鼓手文森退團，新鼓手小P加入\n\n主唱太陽\n吉他手小禾\n貝斯手子翊\n鼓手小P\n\n2006年3月發行 EP 1\n2006年11月發行 EP 2\n2009年5月發行首張專輯“放手一搏Bet on it“\n2013年10月發行 EP 3  奔跑\n\n得獎紀錄：\n2006/07/09 可口可樂鬥酷西門城比賽\\\\\\"Music Battle\\\\\\"年度總冠軍\n2006/07/23 第七回貢寮海洋音樂祭\\\\\\"海洋之星\\\\\\"\n2006/07/29 Nokia百萬音樂起義\\\\\\"第一名\\\\\\" & \\\\\\"最佳舞台演出獎\\\\\\"\n2009/10 受邀第二屆廈門海峽音樂祭＆舉行上海北京巡迴\n\n'),
(14584, '李婉菁 Sandra Tavali', 'http://www.indievox.com/sandratavali', 'http://cdn2-data.indievox.com/indievox_user/30000/14584/pix/14584180X180.jpg?1427771068', 16, 'music, dream, and love'),
(14590, '黃靜雅', 'http://www.indievox.com/chingyahuang', 'http://cdn2-data.indievox.com/indievox_user/30000/14590/pix/14590180X180.jpg?1427771068', 7, '1967年出生於台南，溫柔的雙魚。\r\n台灣大學大氣科學研究所畢業，曾職台大大氣所助教。\r\n已婚，育有一女一男。 2001年旅居溫哥華。\r\n\r\n■音樂歷程\r\n\r\n在校／五歲開始學鋼琴，國小時擔任學校弦樂團鋼琴伴奏及隊長，國中合唱團伴奏、高中及大學合唱團第一聲部。\r\n\r\n研二／開始嘗試音樂詞曲創作、作品第一次發表於「簡上仁臺語歌謠研習發表會」、其中作品「這條歌」被收錄於鳳飛飛專輯「想要談同調」中作為序曲與尾聲。\r\n\r\n水晶唱片歌手／「想起」被收錄於索引唱片製作、寶麗金唱片公司發行之合輯「辦桌」中並擔任演唱、與伍佰、豬頭皮、陳明章等藝人合作。詞曲創作「秋心」收錄於潘麗麗專輯「春雨」中。於文學發聲系列楊逵專輯「鵝媽媽出嫁」中創作並演唱「春光關不住」，同專輯中另演唱「少年彼當時」一曲。\r\n\r\n1994「陳明章音樂工作室」簽約歌手／陳明章專輯「阮唔是一個無感情的人」中演唱「台灣的店」及創作「掌中歲月」部份歌詞。\r\n\r\n廣播節目／「綠色和平台灣文化廣播電台」製作主持兒童節目「綠色兒童樂園」。\r\n\r\n1995／「想起」詞另由林福裕老師作曲，收錄於「臺語創作藝術歌曲集」。與林福裕老師合作多首臺語合唱歌曲，如「秋心」、「看花的人」、「唱呼春天聽」、「故鄉的鳳凰花」、「火金姑」、「昆蟲歌」、「再會歌」等，樂曲譜集付梓中。並擔任第一屆「臺語藝術歌曲之夜」音樂會幕後旁白及「心聲主婦合唱團紀念音樂會」幕後旁白。\r\n\r\n配樂／應邀創作宜蘭縣立文化中心兒童劇團舞台劇「誰殺了大怪獸？」配樂。'),
(14592, '張四十三', 'http://www.indievox.com/chang43', 'http://cdn3-data.indievox.com/indievox_user/30000/14592/pix/14592180X180.jpg?1427771068', 9, '1967年生於嘉南平原西部一個濱海，但不靠海的小農村。本命重二兩八錢，射手座，已婚。電影編導科班出身，崇尚社會主義，相信有外星人的存在，一生在追求「麥迪遜之橋」的愛情。\r\n初夏某夜，有感精蟲肥大，無處可洩。次晨驚醒，發現內分泌如山洪般地狂洩，黏稠物溢滿△褲。他愣睜睜地望著這一片氾濫在底褲的青春異物，仔細端詳卻看似一串串的音符。於是神來之筆，拿起吉他，按圖彈奏，此時美妙旋律，應聲而起，驚為絕樂。從此，他開始音樂創作。時，1989年初夏。　'),
(14593, 'TAKAYA塚田高哉 & TAU Band', 'http://www.indievox.com/takaya', 'http://cdn1-data.indievox.com/indievox_user/30000/14593/pix/14593180X180.jpg?1427771068', 7, '塚田高哉（TAKAYA）與TAU樂團，是角頭音樂Am樂團遠在北海道的朋友。1999年，Am首次遠赴日本北海道旭川，參加當地原住民族－愛奴族傳統熊祭。透過愛奴文物教室館長的介紹，認識了當地的音樂工作者TAKAYA。自此，開始了四年多來雙方多次的互訪與交流。四年多來，雖然語言有所隔閡，距離相當遙遠，但藉由世界的語言—音樂的溝通，跨越國界與種族，傳遞人與人之間最真摯的情感。\r\nTAKAYA與TAU樂團成員包括：塚田高哉、宇井宏、波多也信子、野道玲子、片山紀彥共五人。他們相識於八零年代末期日本的反核、市民運動，雖然大多未受過專業的音樂訓練，且各自擁有樂團以外的正職工作，但樂團成員都會創作與多項樂器的演奏。專輯中使用的樂器包括了吉他、鋼琴、小提琴、口琴、打擊樂器等。他們的作品風格如同Am樂團：自然、純真；歌頌自然的美好，描寫生活的點滴。充滿北海道田園的舒暢快意，在寒冬之時聽來，格外溫暖。\r\n專輯中，TAKAYA與TAU樂團的成員們除了各自演唱自己的創作外，與金曲歌王陳建年交情頗深的TAKAYA還特別演唱建年的得獎作品「海洋」（日語版），在一片翻唱日文歌的風潮中，顯得別具意義。而建年也特別親自寫了一篇短文，向台灣的聽眾介紹這群遠方的音樂友人。建年說，「TAKAYA的音樂，給人最直接的感觸，就是陽光與草原的感覺，雖然沒有激情的吶喊，然而細細吟唱出的樂曲，卻很自然的從環繞身旁的空氣中鑽到自己的毛細孔內，再慢慢爬入最易感動的心情當中，這種音樂好像就應該出現在自己身邊一樣，特別在最放鬆、最自在、也最享受生活的時候。」\r\n\r\n'),
(14646, 'Oki 加納沖', 'http://www.indievox.com/oki', 'http://cdn-data.indievox.com/indievox_user/30000/14646/pix/14646180X180.jpg?1427771069', 0, 'OKI was born to a Japanese mother and an Ainu father. After graduating in crafts at the Tokyo University of Fine Arts and Music, he moved to New York in 1987, where he worked as special effects artist on film productions. He returned to Japan in 1992, and was presented with his first tonkori - the traditional stringed instrument of the Karafuto Ainu. Originating from the Sakhalin Island, the instrument inspired him to relocate to Hokkaido, where he taught himself to play and craft the tonkori. Currently, OKI is the most prominent performer of this instrument in the world. His contemporary approach, which fuses Reggae, African and Electronica with Ainu folk melodies, has won praise not only in Japan, but also worldwide. Through his active participation in the United Nations'' Working Group on Indigenous Populations (WGIP), OKI has developed a network with other indigenous artists. He has collaborated so far with the well-known Native American Flutist, R. Carlos Nakai, the Australian Aboriginal band, Waak Waak Jungi, the Taiwanese singer-songwriter, Pau-Dull (Chien-Nien), as well as Abe Barreto Soares, the East Timorese poet, and the Siberian vocalist, Olga Letykai Csonka. Many of these collaborations are featured on his latest album, No-One''s Land, released in 2002. OKI is accredited as the producer for the widely acclaimed CDs Ihunke (2001) and Upopo Sanke (2003), both featuring Umeko Ando, the renowned Ainu performer of the mukkuri (Jew''s harp) and upopo (traditional chanting). In 2004, OKI toured throughout the US, as well as performing at WOMAD in Australia, with his band OKI &amp; the Far East Band. In 2005 OKI Dub Ainu Band were one of the sensations of the WOMAD festival in the UK, where they also appeared with the highly regarded British broadcaster Charlie Gillett live on BBC London. In 2006 OKi Dub Ainu Band were the closing act at the City of London Festival and the group toured in Norway and Spain. Oki recorded with Irish group Kila on the album Oki and Kila, receiving rave reviews by fRoots (playlist) and Songlines (Top of the World). Tracks from Oki''s Dub Ainu CD have been selected for Charlie Gillett''s Sound of the World compilation 2006 (Rhino/Warner Bros.) and the Very Best of World Music (Nascente). Discography- Kamuy Kor Nurpurpe (1996), Hankapuy feat. Umeko Ando (1999) No One''s Land (2002) Dub Ainu (2004) Tonkori (2005) Dub Ainu Deluxe (2006) OKI Dub Ainu Band (2007) Producer works: Umeko Ando, Ihunke (2001), Umeko Ando, Upopo Sanke (2003)');
