(62352, 'John Norum', 'http://www.indievox.com/johnnorum', 'http://cdn3-data.indievox.com/indievox_user/90000/62352/pix/62352180X180.jpg?1427786210', 3, 'John Norum (born on February 23, 1964 in Vardø, Norway) is a Swedish hard rock guitarist and co-founder of the Swedish band Europe. Concurrent to his role with Europe, he also maintains a side solo project. During his career, Norum also played with Eddie Meduza &amp; The Roaring Cadillacs, Dokken, Don Dokken''s solo band as well as side collaborations with other artists including Glenn Hughes. While living for a few years in the US, he met and married Michelle Meldrum, founder and lead guitarist of the Swedish-American heavy metal band Meldrum. The couple had one son, Jake Thomas, born in September 2004. Meldrum died on May 21, 2008 from a cystic growth in her brain. John Norum is the older brother of the singer Tone Norum.'),
