(85088, 'Joe Ho', 'http://www.indievox.com/joeho', 'http://cdn-data.indievox.com/indievox_user/90000/85088/pix/85088180X180.jpg?1427797862', 6, 'DJ Joe Ho 自1990年於台北當時最大之 Disco 舞廳 Roxy II 開始 DJ 生涯，1992年起於 Spin 擔任駐場 DJ 四年，1996年起與多家唱片公司合作舞曲混音製作，並於1999年於真言社發表電音舞曲創作作品 ''電子中國年''，同時於 Room 18，@live Disco 擔任 DJ。\r\n \r\n2000年底加入 ''theLOOP production''，至2006年持續於台北 2nd Floor 與 Luxy 擔任駐場 DJ，2001年時組成 ''電風扇樂團''，曾於多場大型電音活動中震撼演出，2003年 Joe Ho 參與 MoS UK 與 Avex Taiwan 合作之 Be DJ Mix 混音大賽，獲選為台灣代表至南非約翰尼斯堡進行全球總決賽表演，獲得世界第二名的成績。\r\n \r\n2004年與2005年於艾奧唱片發行了兩張個人混音大碟 ''Resident 001'' 與 ''Trance Attack''，同時製作 ''Trance Attack'' 混音系列電台節目，2006年底應 MoS Taipei 邀請擔任 MoS Taipei 駐場 DJ。2007年底推出全新混音系列 ''Innerstate / Outerstate''，持續成為網路上最熱門電音舞曲節目，2008年 ''電風扇樂團'' 獲選新聞局補助製作首張創作專輯 ''Spinning''，預計2010年發行。\r\n \r\n2008年至2010年 Joe Ho 同時受邀於台北 Luxy, Ageha Taipei, Club Air, Club J2 等各大夜店擔任 DJ，並在台北各大電音活動如 Monster Massive 萬獸派對，Summer Aquarian 夏至音樂節，As One 派對... 等活動持續演出中。\r\n'),
(85364, 'Emily 侯君秀', 'http://www.indievox.com/emilyhaw', 'http://cdn2-data.indievox.com/indievox_user/90000/85364/pix/85364180X180.PNG?1427798026', 5, 'Emily 侯君秀，新加坡獨立音樂創作人.概念深受OWL CITY和日本宇多田 ヒカルUTADA HIKARU熏陶, 創出了自我風格的中文電子音樂。她同時也是自由職業聲優，創作及演唱了日新合作的網絡動漫, がちゃ、がちゃGacha Gacha, 曲目：“未來” 《Mirai》 與“友達”《Tomodachi》，2008年 在Singapore Toy & Comic Convention 及 Singapore Cosfest 台上熱烈演出。\r\n\r\nEmily現下正在籌備發行一部網絡劇《等》, 並創作了同名片頭曲 《等》 和片尾曲《時間旅行》。她也是這部劇的創作者，導演及製作者。\r\n\r\n《等》是結合了一系列的照片的廣播劇，概念順理成章出自於《等》。人，大半輩子都花與等待，從未小事情如等待公車到站或等待嬰兒的出生。等待參雜的情緒可是五味雜陳，興奮，急切，挫敗，無助等等， 也希望歌曲與廣播劇能一覽無遺的帶出這些感覺。 \r\n這部劇有四位重要的人物，它們分別是：\r\n\r\n1. 小樂: 一位懷著歌手夢等待唱片發行的女生\r\n2. 志峰: 小樂的男友，一個默默付出，總是等待不守時的她的男生\r\n3. 偉杰: 制作/創作人，負責小樂的唱片制作，認為離婚是避免愛人痛苦最好決策，患有癌症在等死的病人\r\n4. 怡雯: 偉杰的妻子，認為偉杰變了心卻還是期望他回心轉意的女人\r\n\r\n《等》，一共十集，每集5分鐘，包括一分鐘的片頭/片尾曲。該劇將免費在網絡線上播出,也將會被錄制成DVD發售，而一半的收益將會捐作慈善公益，幫助正等待著援手的人士。\r\n\r\nEmily 侯君秀 is a singer-songwriter from Singapore. Her style is influenced by the likes of Owl City and Utada Hikaru, blending a unique sound of Chinese Electronic Pop. Also a free lance voice actress, she has acted, written and sung on the opening and ending songs of the Japanese-Singapore web-based animation series, Gacha Gacha, titled “Mirai (The Future)” and “Tomodachi (Friend)” respectively. In 2008, she performed at the Singapore Toy & Comic Convention and Cosfest.\r\n\r\nCurrently, Emily is working to a Chinese drama series called Waiting in an unprecedented photo-audio format, for which she has written the OP “Waiting” and ED “Time Travel”. She is also the creator, director, producer and co-writer of the series.\r\n\r\nWAITING is a photo-audio drama series based on the concept of, well, waiting. Like it or not, people spend a large amount of time in their lives waiting, whether is it for something as trivial as waiting for the bus to arrive or a milestone such as waiting for the delivery of a new born child. Waiting can be exciting, anxious, frustrating or even helpless, and I hope to capture these emotions in the song and the drama series.\r\n\r\nThere are four main characters in the series:\r\n1. Xiao Le: an aspiring singer who is waiting for a chance to release her album and perform for an audience\r\n2. Zhi Feng: Xiao Le\\\\\\''s boyfriend who patiently waits for her whenever she is late and waits with her for her dream to come true\r\n3. Wei Jie: songwriter, producer and mentor to Xiao Le. He suffers from cancer and is waiting for his own death. He does not want his wife to suffer with him and requests for a divorce\r\n4. Yi Wen: Wei Jie\\\\\\''s wife who thinks her husband has a change of heart and is waiting for her straying husband to come back to her.\r\n\r\nThere will be a total of 10 episodes of 5 mins each, including a 1 min cut of the opening and ending songs. The series will be streamed online for free, but the two songs and drama series will also be available for sale in DVD format. Half of sales proceeds are donated to charity, real people who are waiting for help.'),
