(95699, 'The Bollands', 'http://www.indievox.com/thebollands', 'http://cdn1-data.indievox.com/indievox_user/120000/95699/pix/95699180X180.jpeg?1427798575', 93, '"Their live shows are energetic, foot-stomping and legendary"\n- HK Magazine\n\n"The Bollands have curated a sound identifiably theirs,... gorgeously melancholic.....the honest, thoughtful songwriting craft of the band still shines through"\n- Timeout Magazine\n\n"I couldn''t imagine a two piece act engulfing a hyper-packed music festival until I watched these guys”\n-Dennis R. Briones, Xtasea Music Festival, China\n\n"There were some really spellbinding moments. A certain observer suggested that it is a new truism in HK’s music scene that whenever The Bollands play, it is good. Well, they certainly did play. And it was good"\n- The Underground, Hong Kong\n\nAlways on the road, New Zealand folk duo The Bollands have been singing their infectious foot stomping folk songs since 2011. With their love of travel, music, good friends & fine wine, They have gained a reputation for their passion filled live shows and heartfelt folk tunes.\n\nTheir energetic, foot-stomping music stems from their upbringing in the folk and roots music scenes in small towns and folk clubs throughout New Zealand. \n\nJoyce, a classically trained pianist, met Christian, a hairy folk singer, at a campfire jam on a remote beach in their home country, New Zealand. They clicked instantly. Since that fate filled night, they have been playing their passion filled songs on the road throughout The world.\n\nThe Bollands have had the privilege of sharing the stage with international artists such as Chris Garneau (USA), Rodney Fisher (Goodshirt, New Zealand), Little Fish (U.K.), The Bads (New Zealand), Sun Eskimos (Hong Kong) and in April 2015 they will be heading to the USA for the first time to tour with the incredible Vienna Teng. \n\nThe Bollands have performed live on Hong Kong''s well known TV show RTHK (Radio Television Hong Kong) ''The Works'' which has included other international acts such as Jason Miraz.\nIn 2014 RTHK Radio 3 asked The Bollands to host and curate their own 8 week radio show where they performed live, and showcased some of their favorite bands.  \n\nNotable Past performances & Appearances include: \n\nClockenflap Festival (Hong Kong), MU:CON Festival (Featured International Artist), Australian Independent Music Awards Finalist, Spring Scream Festival (Taiwan), The Silvermine Festival (Hong Kong), Zandari Festival (South Korea), The Shenzhen Fringe Festival (China), The Hong Kong Fringe Festival, The Grass Roots Festival (Taiwan), The Festival of Lights (New Zealand), \nThree national tours of China, Five national tours of Taiwan, National tours of South Korea, Thailand, Malaysia and New Zealand. \n\nInterviews and features with The Bollands include: \nTimeout Magazine (HongKong) NZ Musician Magazine (New Zealand), BC Magazine (Hong Kong), Fullcup Magazine (Hong Kong), HK Magazine (Hong Kong), Cloak & Dagger Zine, The Underground (Hong Kong), BFM Radio (New Zealand), Kiwi FM Radio (New Zealand) ICRT Radio (Taiwan),  RTHK Television show ''The Works'',  KBS Radio (South Korea) Taipei Times Interview, ICRT Taipei Radio (Taiwan). \n\nLinks: \nwww.thebollands.com\nwww.facebook.com/thebollands\nwww.youtube.com/thebollands\n'),
