(129444, 'Magna Fall', 'http://www.indievox.com/magnafall', 'http://cdn1-data.indievox.com/indievox_user/150000/129444/pix/129444180X180.jpg?1427773602', 48, 'About\r\nwww.magnafall.com - info@magnafall.com - http://twitter.com/magnafall - http://cafe.daum.net/MagnaFall\r\nBiography\r\nMagna Fall is a four-piece Irish/American/Korean band based in Seoul, South Korea. Formed by original members David Holden (drums), Neil Smith (bass, keyboard, vocals), and Kevin Heintz (guitar, vocals) in 2010, they added a fourth member, Kim Taeil, to their lineup in the fall of 2012. They currently have one released EP entitled “Japan” (2011) and plan to record a second, full-length album to be released beginning of 2013. \r\n\r\nMagna Fall\\''s sound might be described as an eclectic blend of the old and the new—progressive rock, punk, grunge, post rock, and elements of electronic music occasionally coloring their sound--the product of which has been dubbed \\\\\\\\\\\\\\"Space Rock\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" by the band themselves as they strive to create a heavy, spacey sound pierced by sharp melodies and riffs. One of the few high-profile foreigner-comprised bands working in South Korea right now, Magna Fall have made their way by making several TV and radio appearances and being included in a host of festivals and collaborations across the Korean peninsula. They have also performed at international festivals in Japan and Taiwan. Some notable appearances to date include:\r\n\r\nTop Band Season 2, TV Competition 2012 (KBS 2, KOREA)\r\nRadio Performances on the Steve Hatherly Show and Shayne’s Music Magic 2012 (TBS eFM)\r\nItaewon Global Village Festival 2012 (Seoul)\r\nHangeul Day Hi-Seoul Concert 2012 (Seoul)\r\nSori World Music Festival 2012 (Jeonju)\r\nRock-do Music Festival 2012 (Seoul)\r\nGreen Groove Music Festival 2012 (Boryeong)\r\nSpring Scream Music Festival 2012         (Kenting, TAIWAN)\r\nJapan Music Week 2011      (Tokyo, JAPAN)\r\nBoryeong Mud Fest 2011 (Boryeong)\r\nGyeongpo Rock Festival 2011 (Gangneung)\r\nGwangju World Music Festival 2011(Gwangju)\r\nCinco de Mayo Show 2011 (Seoul) \r\n\r\n...with much more to come. Look for more and bigger appearances from Magna Fall in the near future.\r\n\r\nFor more information please check out http://www.magnafall.com/ where you can check the band\\\\\\\\\\\\\\''s touring schedule, take a look at recent photos and listen to selected songs and music videos from their album. \r\n\r\nBlossomland Artistic Partners\r\nWireTape Records\r\npress@magnafall.com\r\n\r\nPlease send all inquiries and comments to info@magnafall.com '),
(129555, 'KPM', 'http://www.indievox.com/kpm', 'http://cdn3-data.indievox.com/indievox_user/150000/129555/pix/129555180X180.png?1427773604', 3, '來自日本東京的七人樂團KPM，團長廣瀨拓音總戲稱自己是「哈台族」，而他和女主唱大橋Kiwi的新婚蜜月地就是溫暖的夏日台灣！當時還順帶參加2009草地音樂節演出。\r\n他們的音樂融合日本與南美的傳統樂器節奏，洋溢濃濃熱帶歡愉，同時也思考著關於世界民族議題，將這樣的關懷融入創作，更有一分親切感人的深度。'),
(129638, '一點生', 'http://www.indievox.com/keyfigure', 'http://cdn2-data.indievox.com/indievox_user/150000/129638/pix/129638180X180.jpg?1427773606', 103, '【一點生】\n直指萬事核心的人。\n詞曲創作均以台語創作，\n在龐克的根基下擠壓出激烈的搖滾寸勁！\n\nhttp://zh-tw.facebook.com/pages/%E4%B8%80%E9%BB%9E%E7%94%9F/201429546618462'),
(129666, '傑士塔威', 'http://www.indievox.com/justway', 'http://cdn-data.indievox.com/indievox_user/150000/129666/pix/129666180X180.jpg?1427773607', 80, '傑士塔威 Justway 成立於2011年12月31號，\n以一種像是要趕在謠傳的世界末日年之前的樣子。\n\n團名的靈感來自讓兩位吉他手深深著迷的漫畫人物，\n其中的名句：“傑士塔威就是傑士塔威，既不偉大也不卑微。”\n正是我們對音樂和玩團的態度。\n\n經過幾次團員更換，傑士塔威目前由\n魚王(Guitar), 郭Re(Guitar), 飄飄(Drum), 大郭(Bass), 小洞(Vocal) 五人\n組成4女1男、陰盛陽衰的組合。\n\n2012年4月在樹樂集作首次演出後，\n陸續參加了景文科大熱音成發、大同大學熱音成發、\n台大藝術季，翡翠灣夢想舞台、宜蘭綠色博覽會等活動。\n\n傑士塔威的詞曲創作主要由團長吉他手魚王負責，\n其他團員近來陸續加入創作行列。\n靈感多取材自身邊世界的情緒和事件，\n旋律朗朗上口，曲風多變，喜歡嘗試各種可能。\n\n2013年的夏天，由於團員陸續走上人生的叉路口\n傑士塔威決定自 2013/8/9 起無限期休團。\n但為了在這個世界上留下一些存在過的證明\n在休團同時，發行了首張同名創作EP『JUSTWAY』\n\n不善言詞的我們，\n相信音樂能傳遞想法，傳遞力量。\n曲終，人散，只希望能有一首觸動人心的歌，永遠停駐。\n\n_______________________________________________________ \n傑士塔威: Gt 魚王/ Gt 郭Re/ Bass 大郭/ Drum 飄飄/ Vocal 小洞\nFB:  https://www.facebook.com/justway888\nStreetVoice:  http://tw.streetvoice.com/users/justway888/'),
