(170144, 'Nils Frahm', 'http://www.indievox.com/nilsfrahm', 'http://cdn1-data.indievox.com/indievox_user/180000/170144/pix/170144180X180.jpg?1427774498', 10, '當鋼琴家只剩九根指頭；一場內觀、深思的鋼琴獨白 \n\n在歐洲的當代音樂領域裡，德國鋼琴家Nils Frahm和他的同期Ólafur Arnalds、Peter Broderick、ANNE MüLLER等人合作密切；他們很快就倍受矚目。不像傳統學院派那麼嚴肅拘謹，這些年輕的作曲家大膽嘗試各種樂器及錄音方式，吸引了一群新樂迷。\n\n憑著對音色的敏銳掌握，Nils在柏林成立了自已的錄音室，除了錄製他自已的專輯，也為Peter Broderick、Efterklang等人錄音。在他的兩張專輯作品The Bells（2009）和Felt（2011）裡面，可以感受到Nils熱切探索錄音方式的心，他運用空間及麥克風，還有一張毛毯，在兩張專輯裡呈現截然不同的琴音。\n\n然而一場意外，讓他的左手姆指嚴重受傷，經過四次徒勞無功的手術，還是只能透過復健慢慢恢復。這段只有九根健康手指的日子裡，錄製了這張迷你專輯，並在他30歲的生日發表。九首曲子的標題簡潔而富有詩意，在You和Me之間，只有鋼琴白鍵的唱名：Do, Re, Mi, Fa, Sol, La, Si。跳脫自怨自艾，擁抱自已對鋼琴的熱情；而這張只用九隻手指頭錄製完成的作品，也是他要給樂迷的禮物。\n\n專輯的長度只有三十分鐘，Nils Frahm最迷人的內觀、沈思的鋼琴音色，在這些獨白式的小品中，更顯得質地醇厚。\n'),
(170147, 'James Iha', 'http://www.indievox.com/jamesiha', 'http://cdn1-data.indievox.com/indievox_user/180000/170147/pix/170147180X180.jpg?1427774498', 4, 'Smashing Pumpkins吉他手，溫柔陽光情歌金曲\n\nJames Iha少開金口，大半生涯都任吉他手，披著挑染長髮奏出麻烈音符，在閃光間露出神秘一笑。\n\n90年代Smashing Pumpkins巡迴間，他每晚在下榻處細聲寫歌，其風格類似散落南瓜專輯中的Iha歌曲：行車在雨夜公路上，就著微弱燈光，扭開廣播收聽校園電台排行榜。\n\n十四冬過去，當年浸在潮濕黑暗中的獨身旅者，身子還在路上，早已脫下舊日雨衣。《Look to the Sky》是James Iha的第二張個人專輯，協力樂手一字排開，就是他搬至紐約的生活足跡。後龐老大Television的Tom Verlaine為〈TIll Next Tuesday〉與〈Appetite〉獻上招牌陰狠音符，Yeah Yeah Yeahs的Karen O在低迷電氣曲〈Waves〉撐住甜美人聲旋律，同團之Nick Zinner 的吉他撥奏讓小品〈Dream Tonight〉沉入聲響夢鄉。〈Gemini〉兩段Iha的吉他獨奏，是這位另類吉他巨匠安穩入鞘，卻微微振動的霸氣森光。\n\n車子已經發動，你要不要跳上來？趁著還有光線，我們繞一繞！\n\n如果前張《Let it Come Down》是說不出口的無聲夜奔，2012的新輯《Look to the Sky》就是灰髮中年劍客的公路逍遙遊，他要帶你回到過往那矇眼驚嚇的公路，除魅似的大聲按起喇叭叫囂，最後在草原星斗中安然睡去。'),
(170190, '刪除帳號', 'http://www.indievox.com/enterenvy', 'http://cdn1-data.indievox.com/indievox_user/user180X180.png?1427774499', 2, ''),
(170244, 'HumDog&TheMillionaires', 'http://www.indievox.com/matthum1516', 'http://cdn1-data.indievox.com/indievox_user/180000/170244/pix/170244180X180.JPG?1427774500', 54, 'Over the course of their 2 year existence they have undergone several identity crises; playing countless shows in ChongLi, Taoyuan and Taipei under numerous different names, and covering everything from obscure rock hits to pop classics. \r\n\r\nThey finally formed their own identity when they set the covers aside and began creating their own music. Their efforts were rewarded with a third-place finish at the ICRT battle of the bands.\r\n\r\nCiting their influences as the Black Keys, White Stripes and Cold War Kids, they pride themselves on having a simple, stripped-down sound and infectious live performances. '),
(170408, '美混', 'http://www.indievox.com/mayhwen', 'http://cdn-data.indievox.com/indievox_user/180000/170408/pix/170408180X180.jpg?1427774504', 24, 'Listen to music from May Hwen on iTunes, YouTube, Facebook, and Soundclound.\n\n謝謝！\n〜美混\n\nfacebook.com/ may.hwen.music\n'),
(170723, 'Harmony Screaming 呐喊·哈蒙尼', 'http://www.indievox.com/harmonyscreaming', 'http://cdn1-data.indievox.com/indievox_user/180000/170723/pix/170723180X180.jpg?1427774511', 25, 'Harmony Screaming 是一個以香港和台灣為表演基地的獨立音樂單位，風格元素以新民謠和另類為主.\n\nHarmony Screaming is a Nordic-like indie / neofolk / alternative sound located in Hong Kong & Taiwan.\n\nQuote from review:\n\n" 一定唔係順風順水的另類作曲家。\n\nHarmony Screaming 是主音和結他手 楊艾力斯 (Vodka Lime 2003-2005 , Kissing on the Dance Floor 2006-2009, The Smooth Jelly Club (輕鬆果凍俱樂部) 2010-2012)最新的新民謠音樂單位。\n\n雖然一直很想舉該一個$180門票的音樂會(與紅館山頂位睇齊)，不過寧願觀眾開開心心，拎門票錢買酒，買杯咖啡輕鬆地聽下以提琴伴奏的新民謠(neofolk)好過。\n\n唔知好彩定唔好彩，趕上了幾次大型音樂節的尾班車: 2010台中音樂節，2011 Clockenflap，2012 春天吶喊音樂節。\n係未有雞汁May之前已於2007年應邀回流TVB拍攝mtv(好彩係Beck而唔係史雲x雞汁贊助)\n\n歌一定夠，係驚趕唔切編；有人覺得風格是UK，有人覺得是小清新，有人覺得是北歐風，有人覺得是電玩音樂。\n\n或者最能代表的詞語就是直覺，好可能，他的音樂會低調釋放你心裡面一些幽暗面的想法。"\n'),
(170911, '迷幻的瞎眼約會', 'http://www.indievox.com/blindaciddate', 'http://cdn2-data.indievox.com/indievox_user/180000/170911/pix/170911180X180.jpg?1427774515', 33, 'Blind Acid Date is a versatile garage/pop/psychedelic band from Taipei, Taiwan. The band\\''s lineup includes Nathan Javens (vocals, guitar) Thom Squires (bass) Moshe Foster (guitar) and Jon Snowdon (drums). The members have been playing in Taipei for years. Their former projects include Public Radio, High Tide, The Homo Jews, Collider and Neon. Blind Acid Date is a focused and intense arrangement of thick guitars, shifting rhythms and well crafted songs. The band has been playing shows in the Taipei area and are currently in the studio working on their debut EP, which will be available early 2013. '),
(170922, 'Dream Rush', 'http://www.indievox.com/dreamrushband', 'http://cdn1-data.indievox.com/indievox_user/180000/170922/pix/170922180X180.jpg?1427774516', 7, '活躍于美國加州三藩市的中文搖滾樂團Dream Rush，是由熱愛搖滾樂及執著追求夢想以及來自不同國家的年輕人所創立的。儘管是在美國灣區, Dream Rush還是深信這裡有眾多的亞裔聽眾會欣賞中文搖滾樂。 而灣區的搖滾樂壇雖然以英語為主，團員們仍堅守信念，努力的尋求機會演出中文搖滾樂。他们的演出獲得了贊賞并逐漸建立起名聲，同時擁有一批追隨者。今年, Dream Rush 更受邀與臺灣著名的董事長樂團，一起在美國西岸作巡迴演出，獲得了好評。\n\nDream Rush最初由Freddie和Desmond組成。在他們完成第一張細碟之後，Bryan Klingman, Vince Flores-Snider 和Kevin Lei加入樂隊，為Dream Rush 帶來了更多的創作活力以及更大的拓展機會。Dream Rush 的音樂有著令人激動的節奏和旋律，而來自日常生活的聲音更使人倍感親切。\n\nThe birth of Dream Rush came from the passion for rock music and the pursue of their dreams. Despite what other people think, they believe  there are enough audience to appreciate original Chinese rock music. When Dream Rush first started, it was tough to get live performances due to the fact that Bay Area rock music scene is for English audiences. Undeterred by this fact, Dream Rush slowly build their audiences after a while. This year alone, they toured  and opened for The Chairman Band from Taiwan  during their West Coast 4 day tour in the US. Their music comprises of adrenaline rhythmic melody and lyrics of everyday life. Dream Rush is first formed by Freddie and Desmond. After the completion of their first EP, Bryan Klingman, Vince Flores-Snider, and Kevin Lei became the new additions to the band who contributed more creativity, energy, and versatile tones to the music.\n\n\n2012 - 與董事長樂團美國西岸巡迴\n           宏星衛視特別演出嘉賓\n           台灣青商會特別演出嘉賓\n           We Are Chairman 董事長樂團三藩市迷你演唱會\n'),
(170968, '阿十', 'http://www.indievox.com/panicube', 'http://cdn1-data.indievox.com/indievox_user/180000/170968/pix/170968180X180.jpg?1427774517', 5, '物理 音乐 自由 美梦\n\n\nsishuoliu@gmail.com\n\n@Hong Kong now.\n'),
(171014, 'REID', 'http://www.indievox.com/reid', 'http://cdn-data.indievox.com/indievox_user/180000/171014/pix/171014180X180.jpg?1427774518', 104, 'Reid\r\nHard working rock ‘n roll band\r\nPassionate love of music\r\nEmotionally charged to spread good vibes and tears of joy :)\r\n\r\n大家你好！我們是REID樂團。我們是一個外僱人樂團在台中市！我們都在台中認識！我們現在有四個人，一個鼓手，一個bass，兩個吉他手（他們是我們的vocals）我們愛台灣和愛台中。我們剛剛韓國回來，我們的樂團去韓國有六個表演，我們每年也去春吶和其他的台灣表演。很高興認識你，歡迎光臨來聽聽我們的MV （在下面）。謝謝你們！\r\n\r\n我們的MV（第一個）：http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=EnbQwMsrhUs\r\n\r\n在台北的LIVE MV：http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=n67wsq-ymIM\r\n\r\n我們自己做的台中活動：http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=bxoO2kDznHU\r\n\r\n\r\nWe play all over Taiwan, and you can check us out on facebook, bandcamp, or gigguide.tw to find where we will be playing next! \r\n\r\n我們的Studio Album：http://reiderband.bandcamp.com/album/zoned-in\r\n'),
(171290, 'no entry', 'http://www.indievox.com/noentry', 'http://cdn-data.indievox.com/indievox_user/180000/171290/pix/171290180X180.jpg?1427774524', 30, '<h2>no entry </h2>\n\n<p>Festival band in Japan. There music has organic groove ,electro feeling, <br />\nexperiment and popularity. It invites you to psychedelic revolution and trip to beatitude. <br />\nThey performe at festival in old hippie’s village, rave at southern island,  open air party of mountain, <br />\nart festival in closing a school, club,live house,cafe etc. </p>\n\n<p>And organize ”UNITE!!!CAMP” It’s camp in festival at mountain. <br />\nmany people gather this festival who love peace music that can be intoxicated, earth and party. </p>\n<p>Debut album”daydream trip” released in August, 2009. <br />\nThe collection tune acquires 1st place with the world chart at iTunes store. and used Japanese movie"BECK"</p>\n\n<p>2nd new album”FUTURE WITH HOPE” released in August, 2012.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>\nFacebook<br/>\n<a href=\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"http://www.facebook.com/noentry.japan\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\">http://www.facebook.com/noentry.japan</a>\n</p>\n\n\n<p>-MV-<br/>\n1st album<br/>\n<a href=\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=veOSHW1f4bE&list=UUgGrDDEdBfVSsvAnbmv7N2A&index=17\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\">http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=veOSHW1f4bE&list=UUgGrDDEdBfVSsvAnbmv7N2A&index=17</a></p>\n\n<p>2nd album<br/>\n<a href=\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Y8nfTHhsSG4&list=UUgGrDDEdBfVSsvAnbmv7N2A&index=2\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\">http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Y8nfTHhsSG4&list=UUgGrDDEdBfVSsvAnbmv7N2A&index=2</a></p>\n\n<p>-our festival-<br/>\n<a href=\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=qF79u5r3BCM&list=UUgGrDDEdBfVSsvAnbmv7N2A&index=11\\\\\\\\\\\\