(317658, 'Florence + The Machine', 'http://www.indievox.com/florenceandthemachine', 'http://cdn3-data.indievox.com/indievox_user/330000/317658/pix/317658180X180.jpg?1427777818', 0, '全英音樂「最佳樂評人獎」、BBC「2009年潛力新人」第三名——英倫女聲新貴樂隊——Florence and the Machine，動員Paul Epworth、James Ford、Steve Mackie三位不同領域大師齊力拱盤，以銳不可擋的氣勢直接空降英國金榜亞軍。\nFlorence Welch擔任主唱，同時也是樂團靈魂支柱；由吉他手Robert Ackroyd、鼓手Christopher Lloyd Hayden、鍵盤手Isabella Summers以及豎琴手Tom Monger等人建立起的The Machine，成為Florence幕後強大的支撐樂團。2007年組軍完成，短短時間內就擄獲許多人的目光，2008年的「Kiss With A Fist」和「Dog Days Are Over」兩支暖身作品，皆擠身英國金榜百大單曲之林。尚未正式發行專輯的Florence + The Machine，已率先抱回2009年全英音樂「最佳樂評人獎」，推崇聲刹時從四面八方湧入。坐上BBC的「2009年潛力新人」名單第三名；NME除了力挺有加，更邀請其參與The NME Tours盛會，登上英倫年度超大型戶外搖滾祭典Glastonbury、Reading & Leeds的舞臺。The Guide讚譽：“Florence + The Machine的瘋狂式藝術流行樂將成為2009年最美麗的聲響。” 「Rabbit Heart（Raise It Up）」于首周拿下英國TOP12的好成績，各大傳媒——The Time（4/5）+ The Observer（4/5）+ The Guardian（4/5）+ Drowned In Sound（8/10）——皆給予近滿分的破表推崇。'),
(317659, 'The 1975', 'http://www.indievox.com/the1975', 'http://cdn1-data.indievox.com/indievox_user/330000/317659/pix/317659180X180.jpg?1427777818', 1, '團名The 1975來自於主唱Matthew在19歲時，\n一位藝術家送給他作家Akbar Del Piombo記錄「垮掉的一代」時期掃毒事件的書作「Fuzz Against Junk」封底，\n封底上有著潦草字跡寫下的自殺紙條，紙的最下方寫著「1st June, The 1975」，\n那個「The」的用字方法烙印在Matthew腦海，\n於是，樂團定名為The 1975。'),
(317660, 'Sunrise Avenue', 'http://www.indievox.com/sunriseavenue', 'http://cdn2-data.indievox.com/indievox_user/330000/317660/pix/317660180X180.jpg?1427777818', 0, 'Sunrise Avenue（日出大道）是一支來自芬蘭的搖滾樂隊。在Pearl Jam，Bon Jovi等一班前輩的影響下，樂隊樹立起了標誌性的melodic semi-hard rock曲風。樂隊于2002年在赫爾辛基成立，由身兼主唱、作曲、吉他手的Samu Haber，主音吉他Janne Karkkainen，鍵盤手Janne Karkkainen，貝司手Raul Ruutu，鼓手Sami Osala組成。'),
(317661, 'Steel Panther', 'http://www.indievox.com/steelpanther', 'http://cdn1-data.indievox.com/indievox_user/330000/317661/pix/317661180X180.jpg?1427777818', 0, ''),
(317662, 'INXS', 'http://www.indievox.com/inxs', 'http://cdn-data.indievox.com/indievox_user/330000/317662/pix/317662180X180.jpg?1427777818', 0, ''),
(317663, 'Rammstein', 'http://www.indievox.com/rammstein', 'http://cdn2-data.indievox.com/indievox_user/330000/317663/pix/317663180X180.jpg?1427777818', 0, ''),
(317664, 'Forever The Sickest Kids', 'http://www.indievox.com/foreverthesickestkids', 'http://cdn2-data.indievox.com/indievox_user/330000/317664/pix/317664180X180.jpg?1427777818', 0, ''),
(317665, 'The Airborne Toxic Event', 'http://www.indievox.com/theairbornetoxicevent', 'http://cdn1-data.indievox.com/indievox_user/330000/317665/pix/317665180X180.jpg?1427777819', 0, '2006年於加州洛杉磯組成的五人樂團The Airborne Toxic Event，\n團員包括主唱/吉他手Mikel Jollett、鍵盤/吉他手Steven Chen、貝斯手Noah Harmon、鼓手Daren Taylor、\n以及鍵盤/小提琴手Anna Bulbrook，團名靈感則來自知名作家Don DeLillo的小說「White Noise」一書中的章節名稱；\n\n樂團成軍不到一個月就正式登台演出，迅速在南加州打開知名度；\n2008年初，洛杉磯地區多家流行商業電台和搖滾電台甚至在The Airborne Toxic Event還沒有任何唱片合約的時候，\n就將他們的歌曲“Sometime Around Midnight”加入播放歌單之中，\n隨後包括西雅圖、聖地牙哥、波士頓、沙加緬度…全美各地的搖滾電台也都加入支持他們的行列。\n\n2008年4月，他們正式與獨立廠牌Majordomo簽約，並以新人之姿登上NBC電視台深夜脫口秀「Last Call with Carson Daly」的舞台演唱；\n同年8月，樂團順利在美國推出首張專輯，並陸續獲邀參加「Late Night with Conan O’Brien」、\n「Late Show with David Letterman」等知名脫口秀節目表演。\n\n2008年12月，樂團的成名主打“Sometime Around Midnight”更拿下數位音樂下載龍頭iTunes年終榜的另類音樂單曲冠軍。\n於是，The Airborne Toxic Event的成功吸引了名廠Island唱片公司的注意，決定將他們推向全球市場！'),
(317666, 'Sting', 'http://www.indievox.com/stingmusic', 'http://cdn2-data.indievox.com/indievox_user/330000/317666/pix/317666180X180.jpg?1427777819', 0, '史汀（Sting，1951年10月2日－）是一名英國歌手，來自英國紐卡索。警察合唱團(Police)主唱，1978年發行首張專輯《Outlandos d''Amour》， 1979年以專輯《Regatta de Blanc》登上英國專輯榜冠軍寶座；1980年《Zenyatta Mondatta》專輯再度登上英國專輯榜冠軍，1980年以首張專輯同名主題曲《Regatta de Blanc》拿到首座美國葛萊美獎。\n\n1984年史汀離開警察合唱團單飛樂壇，1985年的處女作《The Dream Of Blue Turtles》專輯問鼎Billboard流行專輯榜6週冠軍。爵士樂、古典樂、放克節奏、雷鬼搖滾樂，靈魂樂、鄉村、福音、民族風等，都融合在史汀多面向的樂章裡。史汀多次為電影創作主唱電影主題曲，偶爾加入電影客串演出。音樂與電影之外的史汀，近年來常為拯救雨林，和國際特赦組織等為環保生態與人權維護而奔走。'),
(317667, 'SuperHeavy', 'http://www.indievox.com/superheavy', 'http://cdn-data.indievox.com/indievox_user/330000/317667/pix/317667180X180.jpg?1427777819', 0, '由滾石樂團 (Rolling Stones)主唱Mick Jagger與前Eurythmics樂隊創建人Dave Stewart、流行女歌手Joss Stone、作曲家A.R. Rahman以及雷鬼音樂人Damian Marley，組成了一支跨界超級樂隊SuperHeavy，首支主打單曲Miracle Worker'),
(317668, 'All Time Low', 'http://www.indievox.com/alltimelow', 'http://cdn1-data.indievox.com/indievox_user/330000/317668/pix/317668180X180.jpg?1427777819', 0, '散發如同他們最愛偶像Blink-182一樣，引領流暢歡愉節奏的All Time Low，成立於2003年，當時還在念高中的主唱/節奏吉他手Alexander Gaskarth、主奏吉他手/合音Jack Barakat、貝斯手/合音Zachary Merrick和鼓手Rian Dawson的這4位熱血輕年，對於音樂的理念一拍即合，聯手打造出All Time Low。很快地他們就被簽入當地獨立廠牌Emerald Moon Records旗下，陸續推出EP“The Three Words To Remember In Dealing With The End”和首張專輯“The Party Scene”。就在完成學業之前，All Time Low又贏得獨立名廠Hopeless Records青睞，送上一紙合約！'),
(317670, 'SafetySuit', 'http://www.indievox.com/safetysuit', 'http://cdn3-data.indievox.com/indievox_user/330000/317670/pix/317670180X180.jpg?1427777819', 0, ''),
(317671, 'The Righteous Brothers', 'http://www.indievox.com/therighteousbrothers', 'http://cdn1-data.indievox.com/indievox_user/330000/317671/pix/317671180X180.jpg?1427777819', 0, ''),
(317673, 'L.A. Guns', 'http://www.indievox.com/laguns', 'http://cdn-data.indievox.com/indievox_user/330000/317673/pix/317673180X180.jpg?1427777819', 1, ''),
(317674, 'My Darkest Days', 'http://www.indievox.com/mydarkestdays', 'http://cdn1-data.indievox.com/indievox_user/330000/317674/pix/317674180X180.jpg?1427777819', 1, '由主唱兼吉他手Matt Walst、貝斯手Brendan McMillan、鼓手Doug Oliver、\n主奏吉他手Paulo Netar(2009年則換上Sal Coz Costa)、吉他手Chris McMillan(於2009年脫團)等夥伴，\n\n在2005年搭建起My Darkest Days，因為擔任Three Days Grace、Default、Theory Of A Deadman、\nPapa Roach、Hinder等知名樂團巡演嘉賓，迅速累積不少支持粉絲，也贏得Chad Kroeger賞識，\n\n協助籌備2010年首張同名專輯『My Darkest Days』，登記加拿大NO.11+美國Top38，兩地雙獲金唱片銷售佳績。\n其中蟬聯主流搖滾榜雙週冠軍的單曲“Porn Star Dancing”，名列iTunes榜「全球百首下載量最高錄影帶」第67名，金唱片銷售輕鬆入袋！'),
(317675, 'Neil Diamond', 'http://www.indievox.com/neildiamond', 'http://cdn1-data.indievox.com/indievox_user/330000/317675/pix/317675180X180.jpg?1427777819', 0, '尼爾戴蒙德（Neil Diamond），1941 年 1月 24 日出生於紐約的布魯克林。他在紐約大學醫學院學習過一段時間，而後綴學從事音樂工作。最初，戴蒙德以作曲家的身份出現並為他贏得了聲譽。 1965 年底開始唱歌。 1966 年，他創作了一系列的熱門歌曲，如：艾爾維斯•普萊斯利（貓王）和"深紫色"樂隊都演唱過的「肯塔基婦女（Kentucky woman）」等作品使他名聲大增。 1978 年，他和芭芭拉•史翠珊（ Barbra streisand ）的二重唱單曲「你別給我帶來鮮花（You Don''t Bring Me Flowers）」在美國排行榜名列第一。 1980 年，戴蒙德在電影《爵士歌手》（The Jazz singer）中的精彩表演使他的明星地位進一步得到了鞏固。'),
(317676, 'Elton John vs Pnau', 'http://www.indievox.com/eltonjohnvspnau', 'http://cdn2-data.indievox.com/indievox_user/330000/317676/pix/317676180X180.jpg?1427777819', 0, ''),
(317679, 'Frank Zappa', 'http://www.indievox.com/frankzappa', 'http://cdn2-data.indievox.com/indievox_user/330000/317679/pix/317679180X180.jpg?1427777819', 0, '成為搖滾名人殿堂終身會員、獲頒葛萊美終身成就獎的一代搖滾宗師Frank Zappa，除了身為歌手和詞曲創作者之外，\n還擁有神乎其技的電吉他琴藝，連貝斯、鍵盤、打擊樂器、鼓也都難不倒他，加上擔任幕後製作人與電影導演之職，\n驚人的全方位才華耀眼非凡！風格跨越搖滾、爵士、古典、實驗音樂等領域，無論是和專屬樂團The Mothers Of Invention合作，\n或是掛著個人名義闖蕩，都在搖滾的黃金年代中立下無數的豐功偉業，更影響了後起新秀的音樂方向。'),
(317680, 'Noel Gallagher''s High Flying Birds', 'http://www.indievox.com/noelgallaghershighflyingbirds', 'http://cdn2-data.indievox.com/indievox_user/330000/317680/pix/317680180X180.jpg?1427777819', 1, 'Noel Gallagher在離開Oasis之後，終於帶著新作品回來了! Noel以「Noel Gallagher''s High Flying Birds」為名，將於10月份發行同名專輯，新歌” The Death Of You And Me”搶先問世， 這是Noel Gallagher於2009年8月離開Oasis後的第一首全新作品，Noel似乎是藉著這首新歌回顧過往的人生經歷，每段歌詞都能深刻感受到Noel音樂生涯一路走來的心情點滴。'),
(317682, 'Capital Cities', 'http://www.indievox.com/capitalcities', 'http://cdn2-data.indievox.com/indievox_user/330000/317682/pix/317682180X180.jpg?1427777819', 2, ''),
(318012, '學韻', 'http://www.indievox.com/zz123123q', 'http://cdn1-data.indievox.com/indievox_user/330000/318012/pix/318012180X180.jpg?1427777826', 1, '------社會不公不義，公民責無旁貸！日後，運動能量勢必持續，或許，一首歌影響小，但我想，­總有人因此受感召，挺身而出！\n\n哪怕只是一個！\n\n一個個的我們，加起來就是很大的力量！         \n'),
(318225, 'Agave Butterfly', 'http://www.indievox.com/agavebutterfly', 'http://cdn-data.indievox.com/indievox_user/330000/318225/pix/318225180X180.jpg?1427777831', 2, '2010/11 組成, 經歷幾次團員更動後, 於2012年固定編制\n\nＧuitar：恐龍\nＧuitar：秉欣\nＢass：蕊娜\nＤrum & ＢeatBox：：開達\nＶocal：謎、兔子\n\n所在地：台灣 , 台北\n\n官方網站： https://www.facebook.com/AgaveButterfly\n                 http://tw.streetvoice.com/AgaveButterfly\n                 http://www.indievox.com/agavebutterfly'),
(318506, '徐哲緯', 'http://www.indievox.com/voter', 'http://cdn-data.indievox.com/indievox_user/330000/318506/pix/318506180X180.jpg?1427777837', 1, '　徐哲緯以第一個台語二重唱團體〝同班同學˝ (古勝中+徐哲緯)出道，後期活躍於廣播界。自警廣發跡，歷經中廣、台北之音等電台洗禮，曾榮獲第42屆廣播金鐘獎【最佳流行音樂節目主持人】獎項，在廣播界找到另一片天空。現為POP Radio FM91.7〈音樂咬耳朵〉節目主持人。\r\n　同時也是Live House熱門駐唱歌手，曾於西門町木吉他民歌餐廳、士林伊莎貝拉風情館、永和樂活健康輕食館、天秤座民歌、永和樂活健康輕食館、主婦之店、街角二號等多家著名Live House駐唱。也主持與演唱過多場活動、記者會、簽唱會、校園等，是位全方位的創作歌手。\r\n'),
(318510, 'Melissa Lauren', 'http://www.indievox.com/melissalauren', 'http://cdn1-data.indievox.com/indievox_user/330000/318510/pix/318510180X180.jpg?1427777837', 1, '　Jazz singer Melissa Lauren has smoothly made the transition from veteran swing “crooness” to songwriter.  \r\n　With a strong influence in jazz and blues, Melissa has developed an original style of her own melting together old school sounds with modern flare. Currently in the studio recording songs for her sophomore album, she will be touring her show, “My Mess” in the Spring of 2014.\r\n　Melissa''s debut album, The Other Side, was released  in March 2012 to great review. A collection of original compositions, the music was produced by Eric St-Laurent, paying tribute to the jazz and swing sounds that shaped the singer’s musical style.  \r\n　Quickly making a place for itself on Canadian charts, the album offers a variety of classic sounds, mixed with modern pop sensibilities.  \r\n　The singer’s love for swing and jazz music began when she started performing with the Toronto All-Star Big Band; she continued singing with them until 2004. She had the opportunity to work with and open for many wonderful musicians; Jeff Healey, Gordon Lightfoot, Renee Lee, Henry Questa, Tommy Ambrose, Peter Appleyard, Buddy DiFranco, Jackie Richardson, and Clark Terry to name a few. She has performed as part of the Toronto Downtown Jazz Festival, Beaches International Jazz Festival, Markham Jazz Festival and Oakville International Jazz Festival as well as Canadian Music Week, and is looking forward to hitting the Canadian Festival scene in 2014.\r\n　For the upcoming album, Melissa collaborated songwriting and producing efforts with Toronto bassist Mark Cashion, and guitarist Eric St-Laurent, and the outcome is a quirky, more playful sound that tests an interesting balance of darker harmonies and more theatrical grooves, coupled with the singer''s signature soft and feminine word inflections.\r\n　In addition to her own music, Melissa has recently been lending her voice to studio work in the electronic music scene. She has sung on five of producer/writer Hibernate’s recently released tracks, one of which was the opening track on seminal pioneer trance DJ Paul Oakenfold’s most recent compilation album, released under Perfecto Records. \r\n　Melissa’s love for swing and jazz music is pretty much imbedded, she refuses to get pigeonholed as just another “standard singer”.  Melissa will be touring Western Canada and Asia in 2013/14, and is looking forward to debuting a more polished,“storybook” stage show.\r\n'),
(318511, 'Renée Yoxon & Mark Ferguson', 'http://www.indievox.com/reneeyoxonandmarkferguson', 'http://cdn3-data.indievox.com/indievox_user/330000/318511/pix/318511180X180.jpg?1427777837', 1, '　Renée Yoxon is a young vocalist and songwriter who recreates and reinterprets the traditional jazz sound with verve and poise.  In only a few short years, Renée has firmly established herself as a musician dedicated to the art of jazz singing. Her latest album, Here We Go Again, has been described as having “torch song clarity with fissures of folk, blues, and Judy Garland-tinged soul.”\r\n　In 2005, while pursuing her bachelor’s degree in physics, Renée began her jazz studies with acclaimed Toronto jazz vocalist Tena Palmer. In 2009, Renée was awarded her BSc in physics, with minors in math and music. In 2010 Renée released her first album entitled Let’s Call it a Day, a minimal and intimate, jazz-inspired guitar/voice duo with veteran guitarist René Gely. This work showcases her clear and unembellished lyrical delivery, poignant song choice, and emotionally charged performance. Physical copies of Let’s Call it a Day sold out within the first year of its release. In 2011 Renée received an Astral Emerging Artist Award from the National Arts Centre and Astral Radio which helped to fund a summer in New York studying with John McNeil, Janet Lawson, Peter Eldridge, and Karen Nimereala.\r\n　In 2012 Renée co-produced an event entitled My Pal Frishberg: a night of the songs of Dave Frishberg. The work received this review from Dave Frishberg himself: “I like your treatment of my songs, I like your singing, I like your attitude, and I like your pianist.” In December of 2012, Renée released her second full length CD, Here We Go Again, an album of original music co-written by herself and pianist Mark Ferguson.\r\n　Recently Renée has relocated to Montreal where she is studying jazz at McGill University.\r\n'),
(318513, 'The Jessica Stuart Few', 'http://www.indievox.com/thejessicastuartfew', 'http://cdn3-data.indievox.com/indievox_user/330000/318513/pix/318513180X180.jpg?1427777837', 0, '　You wouldn’t expect it from a white girl who grew up in Vancouver, but the Japanese ‘koto’ is in Jessica’s blood. Growing up in a household with a koto master for a mother, Stuart also lived in Japan as a child, and came upon the traditional 13-stringed floor harp honestly, taking lessons with her mother’s sensei. Now, following extensive Canadian touring plans in support of their new release Two Sides to Every Story, The Jessica Stuart Few will head abroad for their first tour of Japan in fall 2013. \r\nOn Two Sides to Every Story, Jessica Stuart’s deep musical history and love of guitar heavy rock and soul music are put on equal footing with the Canadian singer-songwriter tradition. Stuart exhibits a pitch-perfect vocal sensibility strikingly reminiscent of Joni Mitchell, with stunning harmonies proudly laid free of auto-tune.\r\n　‘The Few’ launched their sophomore album, Two Sides To Every Story, on March 12, 2013, followed by a triumphant celebration at Toronto’s Cameron House. A couple months after release, it has found its place atop campus radio charts across Canada. Musically innovative and lyrically refreshing, Brad Wheeler of the Globe and Mail calls it, “an endlessly charismatic disc.” The CBC’s Bob Mersereau writes, “It’s a rare album that comes along that truly sounds unique and independent of the rest. Toronto’s The Jessica Stuart Few gave me one of those WTF moments, stopping me in my tracks for a good, close listen of the group’s new Two Sides To Every Story.” The long-awaited follow-up to their critically acclaimed 2010 debut, Kid Dream, the album muses with the theme of dichotomies; work vs. play, right vs. wrong. Lead single, ’Don’t Ya’ was already chosen as a Song Of The Week by CBC Radio One, where it was called “the perfect 3-minute pop song” by music critic, Errol Nazareth.\r\n　Internationally-touring indie folk-jazz power trio, The Jessica Stuart Few has one of the freshest sounds around. The band’s sophomore album, Two Sides to Every Story, was released to critical acclaim, winning the 2014 international Independent Music Award (IMA) for ‘Best Album’ and dubbed, ‘endlessly charismatic’, by The Globe and Mail’s Brad Wheeler. While on tour throughout North America, Asia, Europe and Australia, the band remains in regular rotation on Bravo! TV and CBC Radio while topping campus radio charts, and appearing on commercial airwaves in Japan, hitting #85 on the Tokio Top 100 and #38 on FM North Wave.\r\n　Jessica’s unprecedented take on the Japanese koto (13-stringed harp), her exceptional guitar work, and signature songwriting are innovative and refreshing, earning The ‘Few main stage performances at festivals worldwide. Stuart exhibits a pitch-perfect vocal sensibility reminiscent of Joni Mitchell, with stunning 3-part harmonies onstage, earning the group a spot on music industry and media’s must-see lists.\r\n\r\nThe Jessica Stuart Few is like Stereolab throwing a party with Joanna Newsom at Erykah Badu’s house.  In Japan.\r\n\r\n“Amazingly charming,” – Don Ross, Canadian guitar icon\r\n\r\n“The best of both folk and jazz,” – AOL Spinner\r\n\r\n“The Jessica Stuart Few’s playful indie rock could be one of the most charming takes on the genre to come along in some time.” – Canadian Musician Magazine \r\n\r\n“The JSFew mix musicality, humour, (great) voice, creativity, rhythm, folk, and jazz into their songs. However, …the music remains accessible, warm and unpretentious… Different, and shockingly good.” – Andy Frank, Roots Music Canada\r\n\r\n“It’s a rare album that comes along that truly sounds unique and independent of the rest. Toronto’s The Jessica Stuart Few gave me one of those WTF moments, stopping me in my tracks for a good, close listen of the group’s new Two Sides To Every Story… Stuart has a gorgeous voice, pure and expressive… All that, and the distinctive koto playing, a blend not heard anywhere else.” – Bob Mersereau, CBC Music\r\n'),
(318536, '任俊陶 Dap Jon', 'http://www.indievox.com/dapjonofficial', 'http://cdn-data.indievox.com/indievox_user/330000/318536/pix/318536180X180.jpg?1427777838', 2, '中文姓名：任俊陶\r\n英文姓名：Dap Jon\r\n星座：牡羊座\r\n血型：O\r\n生日：4/14\r\n身高：180CM/64KG\r\n\r\n任俊陶，一個你或許陌生的名字。在台北出生，洛杉磯長大，居住於北京，他是歌手、也是模特兒、演員、製作人、創作者、身兼多重角色的他，走跳於許多城市之間。看過、遇過、接觸過許多的風景和人事物，也結交了許多不同的朋友。這一切，成就了任俊陶獨特的世界觀。\r\n\r\n在面對人生的各種課題，不論喜怒哀樂，任俊陶總是能用正能量去面對一切。透過他的音樂，真實的將自己的生活解構，拆解成一句句的歌詞和一段段的旋律，娓娓道來那些我們都曾聽說、經歷、或是目睹過的真實人生。\r\n\r\n'),
(318773, '金貴晟', 'http://www.indievox.com/joshuajin', 'http://cdn-data.indievox.com/indievox_user/330000/318773/pix/318773180X180.tif?1427777843', 0, '沒有鋒芒與誇張的表達 \r\n真實誠懇的音樂才最讓人感覺依靠\r\n去掉繁複的修飾 我們用“金貴晟的方式”向你推薦\r\n\r\n會表達自已”是新人必需學習和具備的條件之一，但是這似乎必不適用於金貴晟。出生于普通朝鮮族家庭，金貴晟從小與母親相依，做音樂是生活中最大的堅持和向別人表達自已的方式。對於不太會用言詞，但是會作出動人好音樂的金貴晟，在專輯開案和制定宣傳策略之初，這著實讓索尼音樂的工作團隊無從下手。\r\n李宗盛觀察到：金貴晟沒有鋒芒的性格，但是很SOLID。“真實”、“誠懇”、“平凡但是深刻”這些金貴晟獨有的特質或許正是他作品動人的原因吧？所以，索尼音樂最終敲定這張專輯的宣傳策略就是“金貴晟”'),
(318803, '周傳雄', 'http://www.indievox.com/stevechou', 'http://cdn-data.indievox.com/indievox_user/330000/318803/pix/318803180X180.jpg?1427777844', 3, '『時不知歸』專輯，是周傳雄與長年歌詞創作\r\n夥伴陳信榮，集這25年來默契的大成，創作出\r\n了最完整、最貼近他個⼈人⽣生活的專輯。\r\n近年來的大病⼀一場，很多的工作跟⽣生活都放慢\r\n了腳步，於是聽到了「⾬雨打花瓣的聲⾳音」；也\r\n對於萬般事物有了新的態度哲學，就像是⾏到水窮處，「坐看雲起時」。\r\n這25年來的⾵風⾬雨、起起落落，他感念著⼀直待在⾝身邊的愛妻，於是寫出了『時不知歸』；而「櫻吹雪」是今年旅⾏行賞櫻時，⾒見櫻花瓣落下如紛雪，像是遺憾著時間的流逝。\r\n在這第25年的創作當下，周傳雄將最真誠的心情，分享給所有的⼈們。\r\n'),
(318959, 'Live a B life', 'http://www.indievox.com/liveablife', 'http://cdn-data.indievox.com/indievox_user/330000/318959/pix/318959180X180.jpg?1427777848', 0, 'Live a B Life is an entertainment company that aims to make the world a better place through the joy of MUSIC.\n\n新生動力製作有限公司是一間充滿動力公司，發放正能量及充滿理想的一家新公司。創立人"友深"認為音樂可以讓我們認識不一樣的世界，我們願意與你分享亦希望讓志同道合的我們在一起，創造美麗的音樂世界，籍著音樂，同時獻出愛心，讓更多的人感受到音樂的力量與動力，希望透過其創作的音樂，藉以與世界各地不同種族的人分享希望、愛和擁有充滿意義的人生。'),
(318968, '克麗絲叮', 'http://www.indievox.com/christinewelch', 'http://cdn1-data.indievox.com/indievox_user/330000/318968/pix/318968180X180.jpg?1427777848', 1, '第一次聽到克麗絲汀的歌曲，你先是會被她輕柔和魅力兼具的歌聲所迷住，\r\n再來你看到克麗絲叮寫的歌詞，更會對她的信手拈來的中國詩詞意境，融合女性的坦率態度及充滿畫面感的詞句讚嘆不已！\r\n當你聽到，克麗絲叮是來自美國新墨西哥州；金髮碧眼的道地美國人，\r\n用她可愛的自我介紹：大家好！我是克麗絲叮，小叮噹的「叮」，\r\n相信很多人都睜大了眼睛，開始對克麗絲叮充滿了高度的興趣和好奇^^\r\n（朋友和工作夥伴都暱稱克麗絲叮叫”叮叮”）\r\n\r\n而這不過是你開始認識克麗絲叮，\r\n看著她，將會為華語歌壇帶來近年來最大驚喜之旅的開始 ^^\r\n'),
(319756, '奇源鼓手', 'http://www.indievox.com/keeguandrummer', 'http://cdn-data.indievox.com/indievox_user/330000/319756/pix/319756180X180.jpg?1427777866', 1, '"奇源鼓手“ （英文名：KGD） 是馬來西亞詞曲創作演繹編曲錄音製作人。\r\n出生於多元種族與文化的檳城，深受華巫印三大種族的音樂啓發，同時也受本地與英美兩國的名師指點。\r\n長期留學德國後，現在位於卡達爾繼續音樂旅程。\r\n'),
